    "content": "---\ntitle: API Overview\ndescription: Complete API reference for the Sim workflow automation platform\n---\n\nimport { Tabs, Tab } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/tabs'\nimport { Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout'\n\n# Sim Workflow API Reference\n\nThe Sim API provides comprehensive programmatic access to create, manage, and execute workflows. Our RESTful API supports multiple authentication methods, advanced filtering, real-time collaboration, and extensive export capabilities.\n\n## Base URL\n\nAll API requests should be made to:\n\n```\nhttps://api.sim.dev/api\n```\n\nFor local development:\n```\nhttp://localhost:3000/api\n```\n\n## API Overview\n\n### Core Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `/workflows` | Workflow CRUD operations, listing with advanced filtering |\n| `/workflows/{id}` | Individual workflow management |\n| `/workflows/{id}/export` | Export workflows in multiple formats |\n| `/workflows/{id}/collaborate` | Real-time collaborative editing |\n| `/workflows/{id}/versions` | Version control and history |\n| `/workflows/yaml` | YAML import/export functionality |\n| `/workflows/validate` | Workflow validation without saving |\n| `/workflows/templates` | Template management |\n\n### Key Features\n\n- **Multiple Authentication Methods**: Session, API keys, and JWT tokens\n- **Advanced Filtering & Pagination**: Search, sort, and filter workflows\n- **Bulk Operations**: Manage multiple workflows simultaneously\n- **Real-time Collaboration**: Multi-user editing with conflict resolution\n- **Version Control**: Complete workflow history and rollback capabilities\n- **Export Formats**: YAML, JSON, ZIP archives with security filtering\n- **Comprehensive Validation**: Syntax, semantic, and configuration validation\n- **Template System**: Create and manage reusable workflow templates\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### 1. Authentication\n\n<Tabs items={['API Key', 'Session Auth', 'JWT Token']}>\n<Tab value=\"API Key\">\n```bash\ncurl -H \"x-api-key: YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Session Auth\">\n```javascript\n// Browser/web application\nfetch('/api/workflows', {\n  credentials: 'include' // Include session cookies\n})\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"JWT Token\">\n```bash\ncurl -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN\" \\\n  https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### 2. List Workflows\n\n```bash\ncurl -H \"x-api-key: YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  \"https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows?page=1&limit=20&search=data%20processing\"\n```\n\n### 3. Create Workflow\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST \\\n  -H \"x-api-key: YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"name\": \"Data Processing Pipeline\",\n    \"description\": \"Automated data processing and analysis\",\n    \"color\": \"#3972F6\",\n    \"workspaceId\": \"ws_123\"\n  }' \\\n  https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows\n```\n\n### 4. Import from YAML\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST \\\n  -H \"x-api-key: YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"name\": \"Imported Workflow\",\n    \"yaml\": \"version: 1.0\\nblocks:\\n  - id: start\\n    type: starter\"\n  }' \\\n  https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/yaml\n```\n\n## Response Format\n\nAll API responses follow a consistent format:\n\n### Success Response\n```json\n{\n  \"data\": {\n    // Response data\n  },\n  \"pagination\": {\n    \"page\": 1,\n    \"limit\": 20,\n    \"total\": 150,\n    \"totalPages\": 8,\n    \"hasNextPage\": true,\n    \"hasPrevPage\": false\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Error Response\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Error message\",\n  \"details\": {\n    // Additional error details\n  },\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\"\n}\n```\n\n## Rate Limits\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\nCurrent rate limits are generous for most use cases. Contact support if you need higher limits.\n</Callout>\n\n| Authentication Type | Requests per minute | Requests per hour |\n|---------------------|--------------------|--------------------|\n| API Key | 1000 | 10,000 |\n| Session Auth | 500 | 5,000 |\n| JWT Token | 1000 | 10,000 |\n\n## Error Handling\n\nThe API uses conventional HTTP status codes:\n\n- `200` - Success\n- `201` - Created\n- `400` - Bad Request (invalid parameters)\n- `401` - Unauthorized (authentication required)\n- `403` - Forbidden (insufficient permissions)\n- `404` - Not Found\n- `409` - Conflict (resource already exists)\n- `429` - Rate Limit Exceeded\n- `500` - Internal Server Error\n\n## OpenAPI Specification\n\nDownload our complete OpenAPI 3.0 specification:\n\n- [Download OpenAPI Spec (JSON)](/api/openapi.json)\n- [Download OpenAPI Spec (YAML)](/api/openapi.yaml)\n- [Interactive API Explorer](/api/docs)\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [Authentication Guide](/docs/api/authentication) - Set up API access\n- [Workflow Operations](/docs/api/workflows) - Complete workflow API reference  \n- [Error Handling](/docs/api/error-codes) - Comprehensive error reference\n- [SDKs & Libraries](/docs/api/sdks/javascript) - Client libraries and examples"
  },
