    "content": "---\ntitle: Authentication\ndescription: Guide to authenticating with the Sim API using different methods\n---\n\nimport { Tabs, Tab } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/tabs'\nimport { Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout'\n\n# Authentication\n\nThe Sim API supports multiple authentication methods to suit different use cases:\n\n- **API Keys** - Recommended for server-to-server and programmatic access\n- **Session Authentication** - For web applications and browser-based access\n- **JWT Tokens** - For internal service-to-service communication\n\n## API Key Authentication\n\nAPI keys provide the most straightforward way to authenticate with the Sim API. They're ideal for server-side applications, scripts, and integrations.\n\n### Creating an API Key\n\n1. Log in to your Sim dashboard\n2. Navigate to Settings → API Keys\n3. Click \"Create New API Key\"\n4. Name your key and set appropriate permissions\n5. Copy the generated key (you won't see it again!)\n\n### Using API Keys\n\nInclude your API key in the `x-api-key` header:\n\n<Tabs items={['cURL', 'JavaScript', 'Python']}>\n<Tab value=\"cURL\">\n```bash\ncurl -H \"x-api-key: sk_live_1234567890abcdef\" \\\n  https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"JavaScript\">\n```javascript\nconst response = await fetch('https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows', {\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'sk_live_1234567890abcdef',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  }\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Python\">\n```python\nimport requests\n\nheaders = {\n    'x-api-key': 'sk_live_1234567890abcdef',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n}\n\nresponse = requests.get('https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows', headers=headers)\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### API Key Types\n\n| Type | Prefix | Use Case | Permissions |\n|------|--------|----------|-------------|\n| Live | `sk_live_` | Production environments | Full access to your account |\n| Test | `sk_test_` | Development and testing | Limited to test resources |\n| Read-only | `sk_ro_` | Analytics and monitoring | Read-only access |\n| Limited | `sk_limit_` | Third-party integrations | Specific endpoint access |\n\n<Callout type=\"warn\">\n**Keep API Keys Secure**\n- Never commit API keys to version control\n- Rotate keys regularly\n- Use environment variables for storage\n- Monitor key usage in your dashboard\n</Callout>\n\n## Session Authentication\n\nSession authentication is automatically handled for web applications when users are logged in through the Sim dashboard.\n\n### Browser Usage\n\nWhen users are logged into Sim, their session cookies automatically authenticate API requests:\n\n```javascript\n// No additional headers needed - session cookies are included automatically\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  credentials: 'include' // Ensure cookies are sent\n});\n```\n\n### Session Validation\n\nCheck if a session is valid:\n\n```javascript\nconst response = await fetch('/api/auth/session');\nif (response.ok) {\n  const session = await response.json();\n  console.log('User:', session.user);\n} else {\n  // User is not authenticated\n  window.location.href = '/login';\n}\n```\n\n## JWT Token Authentication\n\nJWT tokens are used for internal service-to-service communication and advanced integrations.\n\n### Getting JWT Tokens\n\nJWT tokens are typically obtained through OAuth flows or service account authentication:\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST https://api.sim.dev/api/auth/token \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"grant_type\": \"client_credentials\",\n    \"client_id\": \"your_client_id\",\n    \"client_secret\": \"your_client_secret\"\n  }'\n```\n\n### Using JWT Tokens\n\nInclude the JWT token in the `Authorization` header with `Bearer` prefix:\n\n<Tabs items={['cURL', 'JavaScript', 'Python']}>\n<Tab value=\"cURL\">\n```bash\ncurl -H \"Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\" \\\n  https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"JavaScript\">\n```javascript\nconst response = await fetch('https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows', {\n  headers: {\n    'Authorization': 'Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  }\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Python\">\n```python\nheaders = {\n    'Authorization': 'Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n}\n\nresponse = requests.get('https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows', headers=headers)\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n## Authentication Priority\n\nWhen multiple authentication methods are provided, the API uses this priority order:\n\n1. **JWT Token** (Authorization: Bearer header)\n2. **API Key** (x-api-key header)  \n3. **Session** (cookies)\n\n## Permissions and Scopes\n\nDifferent authentication methods provide different levels of access:\n\n### API Key Scopes\n\nWhen creating API keys, you can restrict access to specific scopes:\n\n- `workflows:read` - List and view workflows\n- `workflows:write` - Create and update workflows\n- `workflows:delete` - Delete workflows\n- `workflows:execute` - Execute workflows\n- `collaborate:read` - View collaborators\n- `collaborate:write` - Manage collaborators\n- `templates:read` - View templates\n- `templates:write` - Manage templates\n\n### Workspace Permissions\n\nAccess to workflows is also governed by workspace permissions:\n\n- **Owner** - Full access to all workflows in the workspace\n- **Admin** - Can manage workflows and collaborators\n- **Editor** - Can create and edit workflows\n- **Viewer** - Read-only access to workflows\n\n## Error Responses\n\n### 401 Unauthorized\n\nMissing or invalid authentication:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Unauthorized\",\n  \"message\": \"Authentication required\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\"\n}\n```\n\n### 403 Forbidden\n\nValid authentication but insufficient permissions:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Forbidden\", \n  \"message\": \"Insufficient permissions for this operation\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"required_permission\": \"workflows:write\"\n}\n```\n\n### 429 Rate Limited\n\nToo many requests:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Rate limit exceeded\",\n  \"message\": \"Too many requests. Try again in 60 seconds.\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"retry_after\": 60\n}\n```\n\n## Best Practices\n\n### Security\n\n- **Use HTTPS**: Always use HTTPS in production\n- **Environment Variables**: Store credentials in environment variables\n- **Key Rotation**: Rotate API keys regularly\n- **Minimal Permissions**: Use the least privileged access model\n\n### Development\n\n```bash\n# Good: Use environment variables\nexport SIM_API_KEY=\"sk_test_your_test_key\"\ncurl -H \"x-api-key: $SIM_API_KEY\" https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows\n\n# Bad: Hardcode keys\ncurl -H \"x-api-key: sk_live_actual_key\" https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows\n```\n\n### Monitoring\n\n- Monitor API key usage in your dashboard\n- Set up alerts for unusual activity\n- Track rate limit usage\n- Log authentication failures\n\n## Testing Authentication\n\nTest your authentication setup:\n\n<Tabs items={['Test API Key', 'Test Session', 'Test JWT']}>\n<Tab value=\"Test API Key\">\n```bash\n# Test API key authentication\ncurl -H \"x-api-key: YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows?limit=1\n\n# Expected: 200 OK with workflow list\n# Error: 401 if key is invalid\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Test Session\">\n```javascript\n// Test session authentication\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows?limit=1', {\n  credentials: 'include'\n});\n\nif (response.ok) {\n  console.log('Session is valid');\n} else {\n  console.log('Session is invalid or expired');\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Test JWT\">\n```bash\n# Test JWT token authentication  \ncurl -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN\" \\\n  https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows?limit=1\n\n# Expected: 200 OK with workflow list\n# Error: 401 if token is invalid or expired\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [Workflow Operations](/docs/api/workflows) - Start using the workflow API\n- [Rate Limits](/docs/api/rate-limits) - Understand usage limits\n- [Error Codes](/docs/api/error-codes) - Complete error reference"
  },
