    "content": "---\ntitle: Workflows API\ndescription: Comprehensive API reference for managing workflows in Sim\n---\n\nimport { Tabs, Tab } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/tabs'\nimport { Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout'\n\n# Workflows API\n\nThe Workflows API is the core of the Sim platform, providing comprehensive functionality for creating, managing, and executing automated workflows. This API supports everything from basic CRUD operations to advanced features like real-time collaboration, version control, and multi-format export.\n\n## Overview\n\nThe Workflows API provides endpoints for:\n\n- **Basic Operations**: Create, read, update, delete workflows\n- **Advanced Filtering**: Search, sort, and filter workflows with complex queries\n- **Bulk Operations**: Manage multiple workflows simultaneously\n- **YAML Import/Export**: Work with workflows in YAML format\n- **Validation**: Validate workflow definitions without saving\n- **Export Formats**: Export workflows in JSON, YAML, and ZIP formats\n- **Collaboration**: Real-time multi-user editing with conflict resolution\n- **Version Control**: Complete history and rollback capabilities\n\n## Base Endpoints\n\nAll workflow endpoints are under `/api/workflows`:\n\n```\nGET    /api/workflows                    # List workflows with advanced filtering\nPOST   /api/workflows                    # Create new workflow\nPATCH  /api/workflows                    # Bulk operations on multiple workflows\n\nGET    /api/workflows/{id}               # Get single workflow\nPUT    /api/workflows/{id}               # Update workflow metadata\nDELETE /api/workflows/{id}               # Delete workflow\n\nPOST   /api/workflows/yaml               # Create workflow from YAML\nPUT    /api/workflows/yaml?id={id}       # Update workflow from YAML\nPOST   /api/workflows/validate           # Validate workflow without saving\n\nGET    /api/workflows/{id}/export        # Export workflow in multiple formats\nPOST   /api/workflows/{id}/export        # Bulk export multiple workflows\n\nGET    /api/workflows/{id}/collaborate   # List collaborators\nPOST   /api/workflows/{id}/collaborate   # Add collaborator\nDELETE /api/workflows/{id}/collaborate   # Remove collaborator\n\nGET    /api/workflows/{id}/versions      # List workflow versions\nPOST   /api/workflows/{id}/versions      # Create new version\nGET    /api/workflows/{id}/versions/{v}  # Get specific version\n```\n\n## Quick Examples\n\n### List Workflows with Filtering\n\n<Tabs items={['cURL', 'JavaScript', 'Python']}>\n<Tab value=\"cURL\">\n```bash\ncurl -H \"x-api-key: YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  \"https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows?search=data&status=deployed&sortBy=updatedAt&limit=20\"\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"JavaScript\">\n```javascript\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows?' + new URLSearchParams({\n  search: 'data processing',\n  status: 'deployed',\n  sortBy: 'updatedAt',\n  sortOrder: 'desc',\n  limit: '20'\n}), {\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY'\n  }\n});\n\nconst { data, pagination } = await response.json();\nconsole.log(`Found ${data.length} workflows out of ${pagination.total} total`);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Python\">\n```python\nimport requests\n\nparams = {\n    'search': 'data processing',\n    'status': 'deployed', \n    'sortBy': 'updatedAt',\n    'sortOrder': 'desc',\n    'limit': 20\n}\n\nresponse = requests.get(\n    'https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows',\n    headers={'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY'},\n    params=params\n)\n\ndata = response.json()\nprint(f\"Found {len(data['data'])} workflows\")\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Create Workflow\n\n<Tabs items={['cURL', 'JavaScript', 'Python']}>\n<Tab value=\"cURL\">\n```bash\ncurl -X POST \\\n  -H \"x-api-key: YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"name\": \"Data Processing Pipeline\",\n    \"description\": \"Automated data ingestion and transformation\",\n    \"color\": \"#3972F6\",\n    \"workspaceId\": \"ws_abc123\",\n    \"folderId\": \"folder_xyz789\"\n  }' \\\n  https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"JavaScript\">\n```javascript\nconst workflow = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Data Processing Pipeline',\n    description: 'Automated data ingestion and transformation',\n    color: '#3972F6',\n    workspaceId: 'ws_abc123',\n    folderId: 'folder_xyz789'\n  })\n});\n\nconst newWorkflow = await workflow.json();\nconsole.log('Created workflow:', newWorkflow.id);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Python\">\n```python\nworkflow_data = {\n    'name': 'Data Processing Pipeline',\n    'description': 'Automated data ingestion and transformation',\n    'color': '#3972F6',\n    'workspaceId': 'ws_abc123',\n    'folderId': 'folder_xyz789'\n}\n\nresponse = requests.post(\n    'https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows',\n    headers={\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    },\n    json=workflow_data\n)\n\nworkflow = response.json()\nprint(f\"Created workflow: {workflow['id']}\")\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Import from YAML\n\n<Tabs items={['cURL', 'JavaScript', 'Python']}>\n<Tab value=\"cURL\">\n```bash\ncurl -X POST \\\n  -H \"x-api-key: YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"name\": \"Email Processing Workflow\",\n    \"description\": \"Process incoming emails and extract data\",\n    \"yaml\": \"version: \\\"1.0\\\"\\nblocks:\\n  - id: start\\n    metadata:\\n      id: starter\\n      name: Start\\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\\n  - id: process_email\\n    metadata:\\n      id: gmail\\n      name: Read Email\\n    position: { x: 300, y: 100 }\\nconnections:\\n  - source: start\\n    target: process_email\"\n  }' \\\n  https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/yaml\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"JavaScript\">\n```javascript\nconst yamlWorkflow = `\nversion: \"1.0\"\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: Start\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n  - id: process_email\n    metadata:\n      id: gmail\n      name: Read Email\n    position: { x: 300, y: 100 }\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: process_email\n`;\n\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Email Processing Workflow',\n    description: 'Process incoming emails and extract data',\n    yaml: yamlWorkflow\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Imported workflow:', result.id);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Python\">\n```python\nyaml_content = \"\"\"\nversion: \"1.0\"\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: Start\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n  - id: process_email\n    metadata:\n      id: gmail\n      name: Read Email\n    position: { x: 300, y: 100 }\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: process_email\n\"\"\"\n\nresponse = requests.post(\n    'https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/yaml',\n    headers={\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    },\n    json={\n        'name': 'Email Processing Workflow',\n        'description': 'Process incoming emails and extract data',\n        'yaml': yaml_content\n    }\n)\n\nresult = response.json()\nprint(f\"Imported workflow: {result['id']}\")\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Bulk Operations\n\n<Tabs items={['Delete Multiple', 'Move to Folder', 'Deploy Multiple']}>\n<Tab value=\"Delete Multiple\">\n```javascript\n// Delete multiple workflows at once\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'PATCH',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    operation: 'delete',\n    workflowIds: ['wf_123', 'wf_456', 'wf_789']\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log(`Deleted ${result.results.length} workflows`);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Move to Folder\">\n```javascript\n// Move workflows to a different folder\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'PATCH',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    operation: 'move',\n    workflowIds: ['wf_123', 'wf_456'],\n    targetFolderId: 'folder_new'\n  })\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Deploy Multiple\">\n```javascript\n// Deploy multiple workflows\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'PATCH',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    operation: 'deploy',\n    workflowIds: ['wf_123', 'wf_456', 'wf_789']\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Deployment results:', result.results);\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n## Common Workflow Object\n\nAll workflow operations return workflow objects with this structure:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"wf_abc123\",\n  \"name\": \"Data Processing Pipeline\",\n  \"description\": \"Automated data ingestion and transformation\",\n  \"color\": \"#3972F6\",\n  \"userId\": \"user_123\",\n  \"workspaceId\": \"ws_abc123\", \n  \"folderId\": \"folder_xyz789\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\",\n  \"updatedAt\": \"2024-01-16T14:30:00Z\",\n  \"isDeployed\": true,\n  \"deployedAt\": \"2024-01-16T12:00:00Z\",\n  \"runCount\": 47,\n  \"lastRunAt\": \"2024-01-16T14:25:00Z\",\n  \"isPublished\": false,\n  \"collaborators\": [\n    {\n      \"userId\": \"user_456\",\n      \"permissionLevel\": \"edit\",\n      \"addedAt\": \"2024-01-15T15:00:00Z\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"state\": {\n    \"blocks\": {\n      \"start_1\": {\n        \"id\": \"start_1\",\n        \"type\": \"starter\",\n        \"name\": \"Start\",\n        \"position\": { \"x\": 100, \"y\": 100 },\n        \"config\": { /* block configuration */ },\n        \"enabled\": true\n      }\n    },\n    \"edges\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"edge_1\",\n        \"source\": \"start_1\", \n        \"target\": \"process_1\",\n        \"sourceHandle\": \"output\",\n        \"targetHandle\": \"input\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"loops\": {},\n    \"parallels\": {},\n    \"variables\": {}\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\nThe Workflows API uses standard HTTP status codes and provides detailed error information:\n\n### Common Error Responses\n\n```json\n// 400 Bad Request - Invalid parameters\n{\n  \"error\": \"Invalid request data\",\n  \"details\": [\n    {\n      \"field\": \"name\",\n      \"message\": \"Name is required\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\"\n}\n\n// 404 Not Found - Workflow doesn't exist\n{\n  \"error\": \"Workflow not found\",\n  \"message\": \"No workflow found with ID wf_123\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\"\n}\n\n// 403 Forbidden - Insufficient permissions\n{\n  \"error\": \"Access denied\",\n  \"message\": \"You don't have permission to modify this workflow\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\"\n}\n\n// 409 Conflict - Resource conflict\n{\n  \"error\": \"Workflow name already exists\",\n  \"message\": \"A workflow with this name already exists in the workspace\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\"\n}\n```\n\n## Pagination\n\nList endpoints support pagination with consistent parameters:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"data\": [\n    // Array of workflow objects\n  ],\n  \"pagination\": {\n    \"page\": 2,\n    \"limit\": 20,\n    \"total\": 150,\n    \"totalPages\": 8,\n    \"hasNextPage\": true,\n    \"hasPrevPage\": true\n  },\n  \"filters\": {\n    \"search\": \"data processing\",\n    \"status\": \"deployed\",\n    \"sortBy\": \"updatedAt\",\n    \"sortOrder\": \"desc\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n**Pagination Limits**\n- Maximum `limit` is 100 workflows per request\n- Default `limit` is 20 workflows\n- Use `page` parameter to navigate through results\n