    "content": "---\ntitle: CRUD Operations\ndescription: Complete reference for basic workflow creation, reading, updating, and deletion\n---\n\nimport { Tabs, Tab } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/tabs'\nimport { Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout'\n\n# Workflow CRUD Operations\n\nThis guide covers the fundamental Create, Read, Update, and Delete operations for workflows. These endpoints provide the core functionality for managing workflows in your Sim account.\n\n## Create Workflow\n\nCreate a new workflow with basic metadata and an initial starter block.\n\n### Endpoint\n\n```http\nPOST /api/workflows\n```\n\n### Request Body\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"string (required)\",\n  \"description\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"color\": \"string (optional, default: '#3972F6')\",\n  \"workspaceId\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"folderId\": \"string | null (optional)\",\n  \"templateId\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"cloneFromId\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"yaml\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"tags\": [\"string\"] // (optional, default: [])\n}\n```\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `name` | string | **Required.** The workflow name (1-100 characters) |\n| `description` | string | Optional description (max 500 characters) |\n| `color` | string | Hex color code for workflow display (default: `#3972F6`) |\n| `workspaceId` | string | ID of workspace to create workflow in |\n| `folderId` | string\\|null | ID of folder to organize workflow in |\n| `templateId` | string | Create workflow from existing template |\n| `cloneFromId` | string | Clone workflow from existing workflow |\n| `yaml` | string | Create workflow from YAML definition |\n| `tags` | string[] | Tags for workflow organization |\n\n### Examples\n\n<Tabs items={['Basic Creation', 'With Template', 'Clone Workflow', 'From YAML']}>\n<Tab value=\"Basic Creation\">\n```javascript\n// Create a basic workflow\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Customer Onboarding',\n    description: 'Automated customer welcome and setup process',\n    color: '#10B981',\n    workspaceId: 'ws_abc123',\n    folderId: 'folder_onboarding',\n    tags: ['customer', 'automation', 'onboarding']\n  })\n});\n\nconst workflow = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Created workflow:', workflow.id);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"With Template\">\n```javascript\n// Create workflow from template\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Email Campaign Automation',\n    description: 'Marketing email campaign based on template',\n    templateId: 'tpl_email_marketing',\n    workspaceId: 'ws_marketing'\n  })\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Clone Workflow\">\n```javascript\n// Clone existing workflow\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Data Processing - Copy',\n    cloneFromId: 'wf_original_123',\n    workspaceId: 'ws_development'\n  })\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"From YAML\">\n```javascript\nconst yamlDefinition = `\nversion: \"1.0\"\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: Start\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n  - id: send_email\n    metadata:\n      id: gmail\n      name: Send Welcome Email\n    position: { x: 300, y: 100 }\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: send_email\n`;\n\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Welcome Email Workflow',\n    yaml: yamlDefinition\n  })\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"wf_abc123\",\n  \"name\": \"Customer Onboarding\",\n  \"description\": \"Automated customer welcome and setup process\",\n  \"color\": \"#10B981\",\n  \"workspaceId\": \"ws_abc123\",\n  \"folderId\": \"folder_onboarding\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\",\n  \"updatedAt\": \"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n## Read Workflow\n\nRetrieve a single workflow by ID, including its complete definition and metadata.\n\n### Endpoint\n\n```http\nGET /api/workflows/{id}\n```\n\n### Path Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `id` | string | **Required.** The workflow ID |\n\n### Examples\n\n<Tabs items={['JavaScript', 'cURL', 'Python']}>\n<Tab value=\"JavaScript\">\n```javascript\n// Get workflow by ID\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/wf_abc123', {\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY'\n  }\n});\n\nconst { data: workflow } = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Workflow name:', workflow.name);\nconsole.log('Block count:', Object.keys(workflow.state.blocks).length);\nconsole.log('Is deployed:', workflow.isDeployed);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"cURL\">\n```bash\ncurl -H \"x-api-key: YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/wf_abc123\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Python\">\n```python\nimport requests\n\nresponse = requests.get(\n    'https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/wf_abc123',\n    headers={'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY'}\n)\n\nworkflow = response.json()['data']\nprint(f\"Workflow: {workflow['name']}\")\nprint(f\"Blocks: {len(workflow['state']['blocks'])}\")\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"data\": {\n    \"id\": \"wf_abc123\",\n    \"name\": \"Customer Onboarding\",\n    \"description\": \"Automated customer welcome and setup process\",\n    \"color\": \"#10B981\",\n    \"userId\": \"user_123\",\n    \"workspaceId\": \"ws_abc123\",\n    \"folderId\": \"folder_onboarding\",\n    \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\",\n    \"updatedAt\": \"2024-01-16T14:30:00Z\",\n    \"isDeployed\": true,\n    \"deployedAt\": \"2024-01-16T12:00:00Z\",\n    \"runCount\": 23,\n    \"lastRunAt\": \"2024-01-16T14:25:00Z\",\n    \"isPublished\": false,\n    \"collaborators\": [\n      {\n        \"userId\": \"user_456\",\n        \"permissionLevel\": \"edit\",\n        \"addedAt\": \"2024-01-15T15:00:00Z\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"state\": {\n      \"blocks\": {\n        \"start_1\": {\n          \"id\": \"start_1\",\n          \"type\": \"starter\",\n          \"name\": \"Start\",\n          \"position\": { \"x\": 100, \"y\": 100 },\n          \"enabled\": true,\n          \"config\": {\n            \"params\": {\n              \"startWorkflow\": \"manual\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"outputs\": {\n            \"response\": {\n              \"type\": { \"input\": \"any\" }\n            }\n          }\n        },\n        \"email_1\": {\n          \"id\": \"email_1\",\n          \"type\": \"gmail\",\n          \"name\": \"Send Welcome Email\",\n          \"position\": { \"x\": 350, \"y\": 100 },\n          \"enabled\": true,\n          \"config\": {\n            \"params\": {\n              \"to\": \"{{customer_email}}\",\n              \"subject\": \"Welcome to our platform!\",\n              \"body\": \"Thank you for joining us.\"\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      },\n      \"edges\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"edge_1\",\n          \"source\": \"start_1\",\n          \"target\": \"email_1\",\n          \"sourceHandle\": \"response\",\n          \"targetHandle\": \"input\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"loops\": {},\n      \"parallels\": {},\n      \"variables\": {\n        \"customer_email\": {\n          \"type\": \"string\",\n          \"description\": \"Customer email address\"\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Update Workflow\n\nUpdate workflow metadata such as name, description, color, and folder location.\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n**Note**: This endpoint only updates workflow metadata. To update the workflow structure (blocks, connections, etc.), use the collaborative editing endpoints or YAML import.\n</Callout>\n\n### Endpoint\n\n```http\nPUT /api/workflows/{id}\n```\n\n### Path Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `id` | string | **Required.** The workflow ID |\n\n### Request Body\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"description\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"color\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"folderId\": \"string | null (optional)\"\n}\n```\n\n### Examples\n\n<Tabs items={['Update Name', 'Move to Folder', 'Complete Update']}>\n<Tab value=\"Update Name\">\n```javascript\n// Update workflow name and description\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/wf_abc123', {\n  method: 'PUT',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Enhanced Customer Onboarding',\n    description: 'Improved customer welcome process with personalization'\n  })\n});\n\nconst { workflow } = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Updated workflow:', workflow.name);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Move to Folder\">\n```javascript\n// Move workflow to different folder\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/wf_abc123', {\n  method: 'PUT',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    folderId: 'folder_active_campaigns'\n  })\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Complete Update\">\n```javascript\n// Update multiple properties\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/wf_abc123', {\n  method: 'PUT',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Premium Customer Onboarding',\n    description: 'VIP customer welcome with premium features',\n    color: '#8B5CF6',\n    folderId: 'folder_premium'\n  })\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"workflow\": {\n    \"id\": \"wf_abc123\",\n    \"name\": \"Enhanced Customer Onboarding\",\n    \"description\": \"Improved customer welcome process with personalization\",\n    \"color\": \"#10B981\",\n    \"userId\": \"user_123\",\n    \"workspaceId\": \"ws_abc123\",\n    \"folderId\": \"folder_onboarding\",\n    \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\",\n    \"updatedAt\": \"2024-01-16T15:45:00Z\",\n    \"isDeployed\": true,\n    \"deployedAt\": \"2024-01-16T12:00:00Z\",\n    \"runCount\": 23,\n    \"lastRunAt\": \"2024-01-16T14:25:00Z\",\n    \"isPublished\": false\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Delete Workflow\n\nDelete a workflow permanently. This action cannot be undone.\n\n<Callout type=\"warn\">\n**Warning**: Deleting a workflow is permanent and cannot be undone. Consider creating a backup export before deletion.\n</Callout>\n\n### Endpoint\n\n```http\nDELETE /api/workflows/{id}\n```\n\n### Path Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `id` | string | **Required.** The workflow ID |\n\n### Query Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `check-templates` | boolean | Return template information before deletion |\n| `deleteTemplates` | string | `delete` or `keep` - what to do with published templates |\n\n### Examples\n\n<Tabs items={['Simple Delete', 'Check Templates', 'Handle Templates']}>\n<Tab value=\"Simple Delete\">\n```javascript\n// Simple workflow deletion\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/wf_abc123', {\n  method: 'DELETE',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY'\n  }\n});\n\nif (response.ok) {\n  console.log('Workflow deleted successfully');\n} else {\n  const error = await response.json();\n  console.error('Delete failed:', error.message);\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Check Templates\">\n```javascript\n// Check if workflow has published templates before deletion\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/wf_abc123?check-templates=true', {\n  method: 'DELETE',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY'\n  }\n});\n\nconst info = await response.json();\nif (info.hasPublishedTemplates) {\n  console.log(`This workflow has ${info.count} published templates:`);\n  info.publishedTemplates.forEach(template => {\n    console.log(`- ${template.name} (${template.views} views, ${template.stars} stars)`);\n  });\n  \n  // User needs to decide what to do with templates\n  const shouldDeleteTemplates = confirm('Delete templates as well?');\n  // Proceed with actual deletion (see next example)\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Handle Templates\">\n```javascript\n// Delete workflow and handle templates\nconst deleteTemplates = 'delete'; // or 'keep'\n\nconst response = await fetch(`/api/workflows/wf_abc123?deleteTemplates=${deleteTemplates}`, {\n  method: 'DELETE',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY'\n  }\n});\n\nif (response.ok) {\n  if (deleteTemplates === 'delete') {\n    console.log('Workflow and all templates deleted');\n  } else {\n    console.log('Workflow deleted, templates preserved as orphaned');\n  }\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Response\n\n#### Successful Deletion\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true\n}\n```\n\n#### Template Check Response\n```json\n{\n  \"hasPublishedTemplates\": true,\n  \"count\": 2,\n  \"publishedTemplates\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"tpl_123\",\n      \"name\": \"Customer Onboarding Template\",\n      \"views\": 145,\n      \"stars\": 23\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"tpl_456\", \n      \"name\": \"Welcome Email Template\",\n      \"views\": 89,\n      \"stars\": 12\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Common Errors\n\n<Tabs items={['400 Bad Request', '403 Forbidden', '404 Not Found', '409 Conflict']}>\n<Tab value=\"400 Bad Request\">\n```json\n// Invalid request data\n{\n  \"error\": \"Invalid request data\",\n  \"details\": [\n    {\n      \"field\": \"name\",\n      \"message\": \"Name must be between 1 and 100 characters\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"field\": \"color\", \n      \"message\": \"Color must be a valid hex code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\"\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"403 Forbidden\">\n```json\n// Insufficient permissions\n{\n  \"error\": \"Access denied\",\n  \"message\": \"You don't have permission to modify this workflow\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\"\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"404 Not Found\">\n```json\n// Workflow not found\n{\n  \"error\": \"Workflow not found\",\n  \"message\": \"No workflow found with ID wf_invalid\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\"\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"409 Conflict\">\n```json\n// Name conflicts\n{\n  \"error\": \"Workflow name already exists\",\n  \"message\": \"A workflow with this name already exists in the workspace\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\"\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Error Handling Example\n\n```javascript\nasync function createWorkflow(workflowData) {\n  try {\n    const response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify(workflowData)\n    });\n\n    if (!response.ok) {\n      const error = await response.json();\n      \n      switch (response.status) {\n        case 400:\n          console.error('Invalid data:', error.details);\n          // Handle validation errors\n          break;\n        case 403:\n          console.error('Access denied:', error.message);\n          // Handle permission errors\n          break;\n        case 409:\n          console.error('Conflict:', error.message);\n          // Handle naming conflicts\n          break;\n        default:\n          console.error('Unexpected error:', error);\n      }\n      \n      throw new Error(error.message);\n    }\n\n    return await response.json();\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('Request failed:', error);\n    throw error;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Permissions\n\nDifferent operations require different permission levels:\n\n| Operation | Required Permission | Notes |\n|-----------|-------------------|-------|\n| **Create** | Workspace write access | Can create in owned workspaces or with write permission |\n| **Read** | Workflow access | Owner, collaborator, or workspace member |\n| **Update** | Workflow write access | Owner, editor collaborator, or workspace admin |\n| **Delete** | Workflow admin access | Owner or workspace admin only |\n\n### Permission Hierarchy\n\n1. **Workflow Owner** - Full access to all operations\n2. **Workspace Admin** - Full access within workspace workflows\n3. **Workspace Editor** - Can create, read, update (not delete)\n4. **Collaborator (admin)** - Can manage workflow and collaborators\n5. **Collaborator (edit)** - Can read and update workflow\n6. **Collaborator (view)** - Can only read workflow\n7. **Workspace Member** - Basic access based on workspace role\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [Advanced Filtering](/docs/api/workflows/advanced-filtering) - Search and filter workflows\n- [Bulk Operations](/docs/api/workflows/bulk-operations) - Manage multiple workflows at once\n- [YAML Import/Export](/docs/api/workflows/yaml-import-export) - Work with YAML format\n- [Collaborative Editing](/docs/api/workflows/collaborative-editing) - Real-time collaboration",
    "structuredPatch": []
  }
}
