  "tool_response": {
    "type": "create",
    "filePath": "/Users/jeremyparker/Desktop/Claude Coding Projects/sim/apps/docs/content/docs/api/workflows/bulk-operations.mdx",
    "content": "---\ntitle: Bulk Operations\ndescription: Efficiently manage multiple workflows with bulk operations for delete, move, copy, deploy, and tag actions\n---\n\nimport { Tabs, Tab } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/tabs'\nimport { Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout'\n\n# Bulk Operations\n\nThe Sim API provides powerful bulk operations that allow you to manage multiple workflows simultaneously. This is essential for administrative tasks, data migration, batch processing, and organizational workflows.\n\n## Overview\n\nBulk operations support the following actions:\n- **Delete** - Remove multiple workflows at once\n- **Move** - Relocate workflows to different folders or workspaces\n- **Copy** - Duplicate workflows with customization options\n- **Deploy** - Deploy multiple workflows simultaneously\n- **Undeploy** - Undeploy multiple workflows\n- **Tag** - Apply tags to multiple workflows for organization\n\n## Endpoint\n\n```http\nPATCH /api/workflows\n```\n\n## Request Format\n\n### Request Body Schema\n\n```json\n{\n  \"operation\": \"delete\" | \"move\" | \"copy\" | \"deploy\" | \"undeploy\" | \"tag\",\n  \"workflowIds\": [\"string\"],\n  \"targetFolderId\": \"string | null\", // For move/copy operations\n  \"targetWorkspaceId\": \"string\",     // For move/copy operations\n  \"tags\": [\"string\"],                // For tag operations\n  \"preserveCollaborators\": boolean   // For copy operations (default: true)\n}\n```\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `operation` | string | ✅ | The bulk operation to perform |\n| `workflowIds` | string[] | ✅ | Array of workflow IDs (1-100 workflows) |\n| `targetFolderId` | string\\|null | ⚠️ | Required for move/copy operations |\n| `targetWorkspaceId` | string | ⚠️ | Required for move/copy operations |\n| `tags` | string[] | ⚠️ | Required for tag operations |\n| `preserveCollaborators` | boolean | ❌ | For copy operations (default: true) |\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n**Limits**: You can perform bulk operations on up to 100 workflows per request. For larger operations, split into multiple requests.\n</Callout>\n\n## Bulk Delete\n\nRemove multiple workflows permanently.\n\n<Callout type=\"warn\">\n**Warning**: Bulk delete operations are irreversible. Ensure you have backups or exports if needed.\n</Callout>\n\n### Example\n\n<Tabs items={['JavaScript', 'cURL', 'Python']}>\n<Tab value=\"JavaScript\">\n```javascript\n// Delete multiple workflows\nconst workflowsToDelete = ['wf_123', 'wf_456', 'wf_789'];\n\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'PATCH',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    operation: 'delete',\n    workflowIds: workflowsToDelete\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Deletion results:', result);\n\n// Process results\nresult.results.forEach(item => {\n  if (item.status === 'deleted') {\n    console.log(`✅ Deleted workflow ${item.id}`);\n  } else {\n    console.error(`❌ Failed to delete workflow ${item.id}`);\n  }\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"cURL\">\n```bash\ncurl -X PATCH \\\n  -H \"x-api-key: YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"operation\": \"delete\",\n    \"workflowIds\": [\"wf_123\", \"wf_456\", \"wf_789\"]\n  }' \\\n  https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Python\">\n```python\nimport requests\n\nworkflow_ids = ['wf_123', 'wf_456', 'wf_789']\n\nresponse = requests.patch(\n    'https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows',\n    headers={\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    },\n    json={\n        'operation': 'delete',\n        'workflowIds': workflow_ids\n    }\n)\n\nresult = response.json()\nprint(f\"Deleted {len([r for r in result['results'] if r['status'] == 'deleted'])} workflows\")\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"operation\": \"delete\",\n  \"results\": [\n    { \"id\": \"wf_123\", \"status\": \"deleted\" },\n    { \"id\": \"wf_456\", \"status\": \"deleted\" },\n    { \"id\": \"wf_789\", \"status\": \"deleted\" }\n  ],\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"requested\": 3,\n    \"successful\": 3,\n    \"failed\": 0\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Bulk Move\n\nMove multiple workflows to a different folder or workspace.\n\n### Examples\n\n<Tabs items={['Move to Folder', 'Move to Workspace', 'Move to Root']}>\n<Tab value=\"Move to Folder\">\n```javascript\n// Move workflows to a different folder within the same workspace\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'PATCH',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    operation: 'move',\n    workflowIds: ['wf_123', 'wf_456'],\n    targetFolderId: 'folder_archive'\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log(`Moved ${result.summary.successful} workflows to archive folder`);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Move to Workspace\">\n```javascript\n// Move workflows to a different workspace\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'PATCH',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    operation: 'move',\n    workflowIds: ['wf_123', 'wf_456'],\n    targetWorkspaceId: 'ws_production',\n    targetFolderId: 'folder_active'\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Move to production workspace:', result.summary);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Move to Root\">\n```javascript\n// Move workflows to workspace root (no folder)\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'PATCH',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    operation: 'move',\n    workflowIds: ['wf_123', 'wf_456'],\n    targetFolderId: null // null means root level\n  })\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"operation\": \"move\",\n  \"results\": [\n    { \"id\": \"wf_123\", \"status\": \"moved\" },\n    { \"id\": \"wf_456\", \"status\": \"moved\" }\n  ],\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"requested\": 2,\n    \"successful\": 2,\n    \"failed\": 0\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Bulk Copy\n\nCreate copies of multiple workflows with optional customization.\n\n### Examples\n\n<Tabs items={['Simple Copy', 'Cross-Workspace Copy', 'Copy Without Collaborators']}>\n<Tab value=\"Simple Copy\">\n```javascript\n// Copy workflows to a different folder\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'PATCH',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    operation: 'copy',\n    workflowIds: ['wf_123', 'wf_456'],\n    targetFolderId: 'folder_backups',\n    preserveCollaborators: true\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Copy results:', result.results.map(r => ({\n  original: r.id,\n  copy: r.newId,\n  status: r.status\n})));\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Cross-Workspace Copy\">\n```javascript\n// Copy workflows to different workspace\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'PATCH',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    operation: 'copy',\n    workflowIds: ['wf_template_1', 'wf_template_2'],\n    targetWorkspaceId: 'ws_client_project',\n    targetFolderId: 'folder_templates',\n    preserveCollaborators: false // Don't copy collaborators to client workspace\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log(`Copied ${result.summary.successful} templates to client workspace`);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Copy Without Collaborators\">\n```javascript\n// Copy workflows but don't preserve collaborators\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'PATCH',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    operation: 'copy',\n    workflowIds: ['wf_123'],\n    targetFolderId: 'folder_personal',\n    preserveCollaborators: false // Create personal copy without collaborators\n  })\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"operation\": \"copy\",\n  \"results\": [\n    { \n      \"id\": \"wf_123\", \n      \"status\": \"copied\", \n      \"newId\": \"wf_abc789\" \n    },\n    { \n      \"id\": \"wf_456\", \n      \"status\": \"copied\", \n      \"newId\": \"wf_def012\" \n    }\n  ],\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"requested\": 2,\n    \"successful\": 2,\n    \"failed\": 0\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Bulk Deploy/Undeploy\n\nDeploy or undeploy multiple workflows simultaneously.\n\n### Examples\n\n<Tabs items={['Bulk Deploy', 'Bulk Undeploy', 'Conditional Deploy']}>\n<Tab value=\"Bulk Deploy\">\n```javascript\n// Deploy multiple workflows\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'PATCH',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    operation: 'deploy',\n    workflowIds: ['wf_123', 'wf_456', 'wf_789']\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Deployment summary:', result.summary);\n\n// Check individual results\nresult.results.forEach(item => {\n  if (item.status === 'deployed') {\n    console.log(`✅ Successfully deployed ${item.id}`);\n  } else {\n    console.error(`❌ Failed to deploy ${item.id}`);\n  }\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Bulk Undeploy\">\n```javascript\n// Undeploy multiple workflows (useful for maintenance)\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'PATCH',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    operation: 'undeploy',\n    workflowIds: ['wf_123', 'wf_456', 'wf_789']\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log(`Undeployed ${result.summary.successful} workflows for maintenance`);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Conditional Deploy\">\n```javascript\n// Get workflows and deploy only those that meet criteria\nasync function deployValidWorkflows(workspaceId) {\n  // First, get workflows that need deployment\n  const listResponse = await fetch('/api/workflows?' + new URLSearchParams({\n    workspaceId,\n    status: 'draft',\n    limit: '50'\n  }), {\n    headers: { 'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY' }\n  });\n\n  const { data: workflows } = await listResponse.json();\n  \n  // Filter workflows that are ready for deployment (have more than just starter block)\n  const readyToDeploy = workflows\n    .filter(w => Object.keys(w.state?.blocks || {}).length > 1)\n    .map(w => w.id);\n\n  if (readyToDeploy.length === 0) {\n    console.log('No workflows ready for deployment');\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Deploy the ready workflows\n  const deployResponse = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n    method: 'PATCH',\n    headers: {\n      'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      operation: 'deploy',\n      workflowIds: readyToDeploy\n    })\n  });\n\n  const result = await deployResponse.json();\n  console.log(`Deployed ${result.summary.successful} out of ${readyToDeploy.length} ready workflows`);\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"operation\": \"deploy\",\n  \"results\": [\n    { \"id\": \"wf_123\", \"status\": \"deployed\" },\n    { \"id\": \"wf_456\", \"status\": \"deployed\" },\n    { \"id\": \"wf_789\", \"status\": \"deployed\" }\n  ],\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"requested\": 3,\n    \"successful\": 3,\n    \"failed\": 0\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Bulk Tagging\n\nApply tags to multiple workflows for better organization.\n\n### Examples\n\n<Tabs items={['Add Tags', 'Replace Tags', 'Organize by Tags']}>\n<Tab value=\"Add Tags\">\n```javascript\n// Add tags to multiple workflows\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'PATCH',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    operation: 'tag',\n    workflowIds: ['wf_123', 'wf_456', 'wf_789'],\n    tags: ['production', 'customer-facing', 'high-priority']\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Tagging results:', result.results.map(r => ({\n  id: r.id,\n  status: r.status,\n  tags: r.tags\n})));\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Replace Tags\">\n```javascript\n// Replace existing tags with new ones\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n  method: 'PATCH',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    operation: 'tag',\n    workflowIds: ['wf_123', 'wf_456'],\n    tags: ['archived', 'legacy'], // This replaces existing tags\n  })\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Organize by Tags\">\n```javascript\n// Organize workflows by applying relevant tags\nasync function organizeWorkflowsByType() {\n  // Get all workflows\n  const response = await fetch('/api/workflows?limit=100', {\n    headers: { 'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY' }\n  });\n  \n  const { data: workflows } = await response.json();\n  \n  // Categorize workflows\n  const emailWorkflows = workflows\n    .filter(w => w.name.toLowerCase().includes('email') || \n                 w.description.toLowerCase().includes('email'))\n    .map(w => w.id);\n  \n  const dataWorkflows = workflows\n    .filter(w => w.name.toLowerCase().includes('data') || \n                 w.description.toLowerCase().includes('process'))\n    .map(w => w.id);\n\n  // Apply tags in bulk\n  const operations = [\n    {\n      operation: 'tag',\n      workflowIds: emailWorkflows,\n      tags: ['email', 'communication', 'automated']\n    },\n    {\n      operation: 'tag', \n      workflowIds: dataWorkflows,\n      tags: ['data-processing', 'analytics', 'automated']\n    }\n  ];\n\n  for (const op of operations) {\n    if (op.workflowIds.length > 0) {\n      const result = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n        method: 'PATCH',\n        headers: {\n          'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n          'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n        },\n        body: JSON.stringify(op)\n      });\n      \n      const data = await result.json();\n      console.log(`Tagged ${data.summary.successful} workflows with ${op.tags.join(', ')}`);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"operation\": \"tag\",\n  \"results\": [\n    { \n      \"id\": \"wf_123\", \n      \"status\": \"tagged\", \n      \"tags\": [\"production\", \"customer-facing\", \"high-priority\"] \n    },\n    { \n      \"id\": \"wf_456\", \n      \"status\": \"tagged\", \n      \"tags\": [\"production\", \"customer-facing\", \"high-priority\"] \n    }\n  ],\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"requested\": 2,\n    \"successful\": 2,\n    \"failed\": 0\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Partial Success Scenarios\n\nBulk operations can have partial success - some workflows succeed while others fail:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"operation\": \"delete\",\n  \"results\": [\n    { \"id\": \"wf_123\", \"status\": \"deleted\" },\n    { \"id\": \"wf_456\", \"status\": \"error\", \"error\": \"Access denied\" },\n    { \"id\": \"wf_789\", \"status\": \"deleted\" }\n  ],\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"requested\": 3,\n    \"successful\": 2,\n    \"failed\": 1\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Permission Errors\n\nWhen you lack permission for some workflows:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Access denied for some workflows\",\n  \"deniedWorkflows\": [\n    { \"id\": \"wf_456\", \"name\": \"Protected Workflow\" }\n  ],\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\"\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling Example\n\n```javascript\nasync function safeBulkOperation(operation, workflowIds, options = {}) {\n  try {\n    const response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n      method: 'PATCH',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        operation,\n        workflowIds,\n        ...options\n      })\n    });\n\n    if (!response.ok) {\n      const error = await response.json();\n      \n      if (response.status === 403 && error.deniedWorkflows) {\n        console.warn('Access denied for some workflows:', error.deniedWorkflows);\n        \n        // Retry with only accessible workflows\n        const accessibleIds = workflowIds.filter(id => \n          !error.deniedWorkflows.some(denied => denied.id === id)\n        );\n        \n        if (accessibleIds.length > 0) {\n          console.log(`Retrying with ${accessibleIds.length} accessible workflows`);\n          return safeBulkOperation(operation, accessibleIds, options);\n        }\n      }\n      \n      throw new Error(error.message || 'Bulk operation failed');\n    }\n\n    const result = await response.json();\n    \n    // Log results\n    console.log(`Bulk ${operation} summary:`, result.summary);\n    \n    if (result.summary.failed > 0) {\n      const failures = result.results.filter(r => r.status === 'error');\n      console.warn('Some operations failed:', failures);\n    }\n    \n    return result;\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error(`Bulk ${operation} error:`, error);\n    throw error;\n  }\n}\n\n// Usage\ntry {\n  const result = await safeBulkOperation('delete', ['wf_123', 'wf_456']);\n  console.log(`Successfully deleted ${result.summary.successful} workflows`);\n} catch (error) {\n  console.error('Bulk delete failed:', error);\n}\n```\n\n## Advanced Bulk Operations\n\n### Batch Processing Large Sets\n\nFor operations on more than 100 workflows, split into batches:\n\n```javascript\nclass BulkOperationManager {\n  constructor(apiKey, batchSize = 100) {\n    this.apiKey = apiKey;\n    this.batchSize = batchSize;\n  }\n\n  async executeBulkOperation(operation, workflowIds, options = {}) {\n    const batches = this.createBatches(workflowIds);\n    const results = [];\n    \n    console.log(`Processing ${workflowIds.length} workflows in ${batches.length} batches`);\n    \n    for (let i = 0; i < batches.length; i++) {\n      const batch = batches[i];\n      console.log(`Processing batch ${i + 1}/${batches.length} (${batch.length} workflows)`);\n      \n      try {\n        const batchResult = await this.performBulkOperation(operation, batch, options);\n        results.push(batchResult);\n        \n        // Small delay between batches to avoid rate limits\n        if (i < batches.length - 1) {\n          await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));\n        }\n      } catch (error) {\n        console.error(`Batch ${i + 1} failed:`, error);\n        results.push({ error: error.message, batch });\n      }\n    }\n    \n    return this.aggregateResults(results, operation);\n  }\n\n  createBatches(workflowIds) {\n    const batches = [];\n    for (let i = 0; i < workflowIds.length; i += this.batchSize) {\n      batches.push(workflowIds.slice(i, i + this.batchSize));\n    }\n    return batches;\n  }\n\n  async performBulkOperation(operation, workflowIds, options) {\n    const response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n      method: 'PATCH',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': this.apiKey,\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        operation,\n        workflowIds,\n        ...options\n      })\n    });\n\n    if (!response.ok) {\n      const error = await response.json();\n      throw new Error(error.message || `Bulk ${operation} failed`);\n    }\n\n    return await response.json();\n  }\n\n  aggregateResults(batchResults, operation) {\n    const aggregated = {\n      operation,\n      results: [],\n      summary: {\n        requested: 0,\n        successful: 0,\n        failed: 0\n      }\n    };\n\n    batchResults.forEach(batch => {\n      if (batch.error) {\n        // Handle batch errors\n        console.error('Batch error:', batch.error);\n        return;\n      }\n\n      aggregated.results.push(...batch.results);\n      aggregated.summary.requested += batch.summary.requested;\n      aggregated.summary.successful += batch.summary.successful;\n      aggregated.summary.failed += batch.summary.failed;\n    });\n\n    return aggregated;\n  }\n}\n\n// Usage\nconst bulkManager = new BulkOperationManager('YOUR_API_KEY');\n\n// Process 500 workflows in batches of 100\nconst result = await bulkManager.executeBulkOperation('deploy', largWorkflowIdList);\nconsole.log(`Processed ${result.summary.successful} out of ${result.summary.requested} workflows`);\n```\n\n### Workflow Migration\n\nComplete example for migrating workflows between environments:\n\n```javascript\nasync function migrateWorkflows(sourceWorkspaceId, targetWorkspaceId, options = {}) {\n  const {\n    folderMapping = {},\n    preserveDeploymentStatus = false,\n    tagPrefix = 'migrated',\n    dryRun = false\n  } = options;\n\n  console.log(`${dryRun ? 'Dry run: ' : ''}Migrating workflows from ${sourceWorkspaceId} to ${targetWorkspaceId}`);\n\n  // 1. Get all workflows from source workspace\n  const sourceResponse = await fetch('/api/workflows?' + new URLSearchParams({\n    workspaceId: sourceWorkspaceId,\n    limit: '100'\n  }), {\n    headers: { 'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY' }\n  });\n\n  const { data: sourceWorkflows } = await sourceResponse.json();\n  console.log(`Found ${sourceWorkflows.length} workflows to migrate`);\n\n  if (dryRun) {\n    console.log('Workflows to migrate:', sourceWorkflows.map(w => w.name));\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // 2. Copy workflows to target workspace\n  const workflowIds = sourceWorkflows.map(w => w.id);\n  const copyResult = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n    method: 'PATCH',\n    headers: {\n      'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      operation: 'copy',\n      workflowIds,\n      targetWorkspaceId,\n      targetFolderId: folderMapping.default || null,\n      preserveCollaborators: false // Don't copy collaborators in migration\n    })\n  });\n\n  const copyResults = await copyResult.json();\n  const newWorkflowIds = copyResults.results\n    .filter(r => r.status === 'copied')\n    .map(r => r.newId);\n\n  console.log(`Successfully copied ${newWorkflowIds.length} workflows`);\n\n  // 3. Add migration tags\n  if (newWorkflowIds.length > 0) {\n    await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n      method: 'PATCH',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        operation: 'tag',\n        workflowIds: newWorkflowIds,\n        tags: [tagPrefix, `source-${sourceWorkspaceId}`, new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0]]\n      })\n    });\n  }\n\n  // 4. Deploy if preserving deployment status\n  if (preserveDeploymentStatus) {\n    const deployedSourceIds = sourceWorkflows\n      .filter(w => w.isDeployed)\n      .map(w => w.id);\n    \n    if (deployedSourceIds.length > 0) {\n      // Find corresponding copied workflow IDs\n      const deployIds = copyResults.results\n        .filter(r => r.status === 'copied' && deployedSourceIds.includes(r.id))\n        .map(r => r.newId);\n\n      if (deployIds.length > 0) {\n        await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n          method: 'PATCH',\n          headers: {\n            'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n            'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n          },\n          body: JSON.stringify({\n            operation: 'deploy',\n            workflowIds: deployIds\n          })\n        });\n\n        console.log(`Deployed ${deployIds.length} workflows to maintain status`);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  return {\n    sourceWorkflows: sourceWorkflows.length,\n    copiedWorkflows: newWorkflowIds.length,\n    failedCopies: copyResults.summary.failed,\n    newWorkflowIds\n  };\n}\n\n// Usage\nconst migrationResult = await migrateWorkflows('ws_dev', 'ws_staging', {\n  preserveDeploymentStatus: true,\n  tagPrefix: 'staging-migration',\n  dryRun: false\n});\n\nconsole.log('Migration completed:', migrationResult);\n```\n\n## Best Practices\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n**Performance Tips**\n- Limit bulk operations to 100 workflows per request\n- Add delays between large batch operations to avoid rate limits\n- Use specific error handling for partial failures\n- Always verify results before proceeding with additional operations\n</Callout>\n\n### Bulk Operation Guidelines\n\n1. **Verify Permissions** - Ensure you have appropriate permissions for all target workflows\n2. **Backup Important Data** - Export workflows before destructive operations\n3. **Test with Small Batches** - Start with a few workflows to verify behavior\n4. **Monitor Results** - Check the summary and individual results for each operation\n5. **Handle Partial Failures** - Plan for scenarios where some workflows fail\n6. **Use Dry Run Options** - When available, test operations without making changes\n\n### Common Patterns\n\n```javascript\n// Pattern 1: Safe bulk delete with confirmation\nasync function safeBulkDelete(workflowIds) {\n  console.log(`Preparing to delete ${workflowIds.length} workflows`);\n  \n  // Get workflow names for confirmation\n  const workflows = await Promise.all(\n    workflowIds.map(id => \n      fetch(`/api/workflows/${id}`, {\n        headers: { 'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY' }\n      }).then(r => r.json()).then(data => data.data)\n    )\n  );\n  \n  console.log('Workflows to delete:');\n  workflows.forEach(w => console.log(`- ${w.name} (${w.runCount} runs)`));\n  \n  const confirmed = confirm(`Delete ${workflows.length} workflows? This cannot be undone.`);\n  if (!confirmed) return;\n  \n  const result = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n    method: 'PATCH',\n    headers: {\n      'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      operation: 'delete',\n      workflowIds\n    })\n  });\n  \n  return result.json();\n}\n\n// Pattern 2: Conditional bulk operations\nasync function archiveInactiveWorkflows(days = 30) {\n  const cutoffDate = new Date(Date.now() - days * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000).toISOString();\n  \n  // Find inactive workflows\n  const response = await fetch('/api/workflows?' + new URLSearchParams({\n    updatedBefore: cutoffDate,\n    status: 'deployed',\n    maxRunCount: '0',\n    limit: '100'\n  }), {\n    headers: { 'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY' }\n  });\n  \n  const { data: inactiveWorkflows } = await response.json();\n  \n  if (inactiveWorkflows.length === 0) {\n    console.log('No inactive workflows found');\n    return;\n  }\n  \n  console.log(`Found ${inactiveWorkflows.length} inactive workflows`);\n  \n  // Move to archive folder and undeploy\n  const workflowIds = inactiveWorkflows.map(w => w.id);\n  \n  const [moveResult, undeployResult, tagResult] = await Promise.all([\n    // Move to archive folder\n    fetch('/api/workflows', {\n      method: 'PATCH',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        operation: 'move',\n        workflowIds,\n        targetFolderId: 'folder_archive'\n      })\n    }).then(r => r.json()),\n    \n    // Undeploy\n    fetch('/api/workflows', {\n      method: 'PATCH',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        operation: 'undeploy',\n        workflowIds\n      })\n    }).then(r => r.json()),\n    \n    // Add archived tag\n    fetch('/api/workflows', {\n      method: 'PATCH',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        operation: 'tag',\n        workflowIds,\n        tags: ['archived', `archived-${new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0]}`]\n      })\n    }).then(r => r.json())\n  ]);\n  \n  console.log('Archive results:', {\n    moved: moveResult.summary.successful,\n    undeployed: undeployResult.summary.successful,\n    tagged: tagResult.summary.successful\n  });\n}\n```\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [YAML Import/Export](/docs/api/workflows/yaml-import-export) - Work with YAML workflow definitions\n- [Validation](/docs/api/workflows/validation) - Validate workflows before operations\n- [Export Formats](/docs/api/workflows/export-formats) - Export workflows in multiple formats\n- [Error Codes](/docs/api/error-codes) - Complete error handling reference",
    "structuredPatch": []
  }
}
