    "file_path": "/Users/jeremyparker/Desktop/Claude Coding Projects/sim/apps/docs/content/docs/api/workflows/yaml-import-export.mdx",
    "content": "---\ntitle: YAML Import/Export\ndescription: Create and update workflows using YAML format for version control and programmatic management\n---\n\nimport { Tabs, Tab } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/tabs'\nimport { Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout'\n\n# YAML Import/Export\n\nThe Sim API supports importing and exporting workflows in YAML format, enabling version control, programmatic workflow management, and easy sharing of workflow definitions. YAML format provides a human-readable, text-based representation of your workflows.\n\n## Overview\n\nYAML workflow operations include:\n\n- **Import from YAML** - Create new workflows from YAML definitions\n- **Update from YAML** - Update existing workflows with YAML\n- **Validation Only** - Validate YAML without creating workflows\n- **Layout Generation** - Automatically position blocks when importing\n- **ID Preservation** - Maintain workflow and block IDs across imports\n\n## Import Workflow from YAML\n\nCreate a new workflow from a YAML definition.\n\n### Endpoint\n\n```http\nPOST /api/workflows/yaml\n```\n\n### Request Body\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"string (required)\",\n  \"description\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"color\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"workspaceId\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"folderId\": \"string | null (optional)\",\n  \"yaml\": \"string (required)\",\n  \"preserveIds\": \"boolean (default: false)\",\n  \"overwriteExisting\": \"boolean (default: false)\",\n  \"validateOnly\": \"boolean (default: false)\"\n}\n```\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `name` | string | - | **Required.** Name for the new workflow |\n| `description` | string | `\"\"` | Optional description |\n| `color` | string | `\"#3972F6\"` | Hex color code |\n| `workspaceId` | string | - | Target workspace ID |\n| `folderId` | string\\|null | - | Target folder ID |\n| `yaml` | string | - | **Required.** YAML workflow definition |\n| `preserveIds` | boolean | `false` | Keep original workflow/block IDs |\n| `overwriteExisting` | boolean | `false` | Overwrite existing workflow if ID matches |\n| `validateOnly` | boolean | `false` | Only validate, don't create workflow |\n\n### YAML Structure\n\nA typical workflow YAML structure:\n\n```yaml\nversion: \"1.0\"\nmetadata:\n  name: \"Email Processing Workflow\"\n  description: \"Process incoming emails and extract data\"\n  color: \"#10B981\"\n\nvariables:\n  customer_email:\n    type: string\n    description: \"Customer email address\"\n  processed_count:\n    type: number\n    description: \"Number of emails processed\"\n    default: 0\n\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Start\"\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        startWorkflow: \"webhook\"\n        webhookPath: \"/process-email\"\n    outputs:\n      response:\n        type: { input: \"any\" }\n    \n  - id: read_email\n    metadata:\n      id: gmail\n      name: \"Read Email\"\n    position: { x: 350, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        messageId: \"{{webhook.messageId}}\"\n        markAsRead: true\n    outputs:\n      subject:\n        type: { input: \"string\" }\n      body:\n        type: { input: \"string\" }\n      sender:\n        type: { input: \"string\" }\n        \n  - id: extract_data\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Extract Customer Data\"\n    position: { x: 600, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        code: |\n          // Extract customer information from email\n          const emailBody = inputs.body;\n          const customerMatch = emailBody.match(/customer:\\s*(\\S+@\\S+)/i);\n          const customer_email = customerMatch ? customerMatch[1] : null;\n          \n          return { customer_email };\n    outputs:\n      customer_email:\n        type: { input: \"string\" }\n\n  - id: send_response\n    metadata:\n      id: gmail\n      name: \"Send Response\"\n    position: { x: 850, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        to: \"{{extract_data.customer_email}}\"\n        subject: \"Re: {{read_email.subject}}\"\n        body: \"Thank you for your email. We'll process your request shortly.\"\n\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: read_email\n    sourceHandle: response\n    targetHandle: input\n    \n  - source: read_email\n    target: extract_data\n    sourceHandle: body\n    targetHandle: input\n    \n  - source: extract_data\n    target: send_response\n    sourceHandle: customer_email\n    targetHandle: input\n\nloops: {}\nparallels: {}\n```\n\n### Examples\n\n<Tabs items={['Basic Import', 'Validation Only', 'Advanced Import', 'Overwrite Existing']}>\n<Tab value=\"Basic Import\">\n```javascript\nconst yamlWorkflow = `\nversion: \"1.0\"\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: Start\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n  - id: send_welcome\n    metadata:\n      id: gmail\n      name: Send Welcome Email\n    position: { x: 300, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        to: \"{{customer_email}}\"\n        subject: \"Welcome!\"\n        body: \"Thank you for joining us.\"\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: send_welcome\nvariables:\n  customer_email:\n    type: string\n`;\n\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Welcome Email Workflow',\n    description: 'Send welcome emails to new customers',\n    color: '#10B981',\n    yaml: yamlWorkflow\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Created workflow:', result.id);\nconsole.log('Import summary:', result.summary);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Validation Only\">\n```javascript\n// Validate YAML without creating workflow\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Test Workflow',\n    yaml: yamlContent,\n    validateOnly: true\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\n\nif (result.valid) {\n  console.log('YAML is valid!');\n  console.log('Summary:', result.summary);\n  console.log('Parsed workflow has:', {\n    blocks: result.workflow.blocks?.length || 0,\n    connections: result.workflow.connections?.length || 0,\n    variables: Object.keys(result.workflow.variables || {}).length\n  });\n} else {\n  console.error('YAML validation failed:', result.validationErrors);\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Advanced Import\">\n```javascript\n// Import with advanced options\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Customer Support Automation',\n    description: 'Handle customer support tickets automatically',\n    color: '#8B5CF6',\n    workspaceId: 'ws_customer_service',\n    folderId: 'folder_automation',\n    yaml: complexYamlWorkflow,\n    preserveIds: true, // Keep original block IDs\n    overwriteExisting: false\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Advanced import results:', {\n  workflowId: result.id,\n  blocksCreated: result.summary.blocks,\n  connectionsCreated: result.summary.connections,\n  importTime: result.importTime\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Overwrite Existing\">\n```javascript\n// Import and overwrite existing workflow\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Updated Workflow',\n    yaml: updatedYamlContent,\n    preserveIds: true,\n    overwriteExisting: true // This will replace existing workflow with same ID\n  })\n});\n\nif (response.ok) {\n  const result = await response.json();\n  console.log('Successfully updated workflow:', result.id);\n} else {\n  const error = await response.json();\n  console.error('Import failed:', error.details);\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Response\n\n#### Successful Import\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"wf_abc123\",\n  \"name\": \"Welcome Email Workflow\",\n  \"description\": \"Send welcome emails to new customers\",\n  \"color\": \"#10B981\",\n  \"workspaceId\": \"ws_abc123\",\n  \"folderId\": null,\n  \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\",\n  \"updatedAt\": \"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\",\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"blocks\": 2,\n    \"connections\": 1,\n    \"loops\": 0,\n    \"parallels\": 0\n  },\n  \"importTime\": 1250\n}\n```\n\n#### Validation Only Response\n```json\n{\n  \"valid\": true,\n  \"workflow\": {\n    \"blocks\": [\n      // Parsed block objects\n    ],\n    \"connections\": [\n      // Parsed connection objects\n    ],\n    \"variables\": {}\n  },\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"blocks\": 2,\n    \"connections\": 1,\n    \"loops\": 0,\n    \"parallels\": 0\n  },\n  \"validationTime\": 450\n}\n```\n\n## Update Workflow from YAML\n\nUpdate an existing workflow with a new YAML definition.\n\n### Endpoint\n\n```http\nPUT /api/workflows/yaml?id={workflowId}\n```\n\n### Query Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `id` | string | **Required.** The workflow ID to update |\n\n### Request Body\n\n```json\n{\n  \"yaml\": \"string (required)\",\n  \"preserveMetadata\": \"boolean (default: true)\",\n  \"createCheckpoint\": \"boolean (default: true)\",\n  \"validateBeforeUpdate\": \"boolean (default: true)\"\n}\n```\n\n### Examples\n\n<Tabs items={['Update Workflow', 'Replace Structure', 'Safe Update']}>\n<Tab value=\"Update Workflow\">\n```javascript\n// Update existing workflow with new YAML\nconst updatedYaml = `\nversion: \"1.0\"\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: Start\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n  - id: process_data\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: Process Customer Data\n    position: { x: 300, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        code: |\n          // Enhanced processing logic\n          const data = inputs.customerData;\n          const processed = {\n            ...data,\n            processed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n            score: calculateScore(data)\n          };\n          return processed;\n  - id: send_notification\n    metadata:\n      id: slack\n      name: Send Notification\n    position: { x: 500, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        channel: \"#customer-updates\"\n        text: \"New customer processed: {{process_data.name}}\"\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: process_data\n  - source: process_data\n    target: send_notification\n`;\n\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml?id=wf_abc123', {\n  method: 'PUT',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    yaml: updatedYaml,\n    preserveMetadata: true,\n    createCheckpoint: true,\n    validateBeforeUpdate: true\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Update summary:', result.summary);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Replace Structure\">\n```javascript\n// Completely replace workflow structure\nconst newStructure = `\nversion: \"1.0\"\n# Completely new workflow structure\nblocks:\n  - id: webhook_trigger\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: Webhook Trigger\n    position: { x: 50, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        startWorkflow: webhook\n        webhookPath: \"/new-endpoint\"\n  \n  - id: parallel_processor\n    metadata:\n      id: parallel\n      name: Process Multiple Items\n    position: { x: 250, y: 100 }\n    \n  - id: final_response\n    metadata:\n      id: response\n      name: Send Response\n    position: { x: 450, y: 100 }\n\nconnections:\n  - source: webhook_trigger\n    target: parallel_processor\n  - source: parallel_processor\n    target: final_response\n\nparallels:\n  parallel_processor:\n    config:\n      branches:\n        - name: \"Email Processing\"\n          blocks: [\"email_block\"]\n        - name: \"Data Processing\" \n          blocks: [\"data_block\"]\n`;\n\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml?id=wf_abc123', {\n  method: 'PUT',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    yaml: newStructure,\n    preserveMetadata: false, // Allow workflow name/description to be updated from YAML\n    createCheckpoint: true,\n    validateBeforeUpdate: true\n  })\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Safe Update\">\n```javascript\n// Safe update with validation and error handling\nasync function safeUpdateWorkflow(workflowId, yamlContent) {\n  try {\n    // First, validate the YAML\n    const validationResponse = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        name: 'temp',\n        yaml: yamlContent,\n        validateOnly: true\n      })\n    });\n\n    const validation = await validationResponse.json();\n    \n    if (!validation.valid) {\n      console.error('YAML validation failed:', validation.validationErrors);\n      return { success: false, errors: validation.validationErrors };\n    }\n\n    console.log('YAML validation passed');\n\n    // Now perform the update\n    const updateResponse = await fetch(`/api/workflows/yaml?id=${workflowId}`, {\n      method: 'PUT',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        yaml: yamlContent,\n        preserveMetadata: true,\n        createCheckpoint: true,\n        validateBeforeUpdate: true\n      })\n    });\n\n    if (!updateResponse.ok) {\n      const error = await updateResponse.json();\n      console.error('Update failed:', error);\n      return { success: false, error: error.message };\n    }\n\n    const result = await updateResponse.json();\n    console.log('Workflow updated successfully:', result.summary);\n    \n    return { success: true, result };\n\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('Update failed with exception:', error);\n    return { success: false, error: error.message };\n  }\n}\n\n// Usage\nconst updateResult = await safeUpdateWorkflow('wf_abc123', newYamlContent);\nif (!updateResult.success) {\n  console.error('Failed to update workflow:', updateResult.error || updateResult.errors);\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"wf_abc123\",\n  \"updated\": true,\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"blocks\": 3,\n    \"connections\": 2,\n    \"loops\": 0,\n    \"parallels\": 1\n  },\n  \"updateTime\": 890\n}\n```\n\n## YAML Validation\n\nValidate YAML workflow definitions without creating or updating workflows.\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\nUse validation to test YAML definitions before importing or updating workflows. This helps catch errors early and ensures smooth imports.\n</Callout>\n\n### Validation Process\n\nThe validation process checks for:\n\n- **YAML Syntax** - Valid YAML format\n- **Schema Compliance** - Correct workflow structure\n- **Block Configuration** - Valid block types and parameters\n- **Connection Validity** - Proper source/target references\n- **Variable Dependencies** - Variable references and types\n- **Tool Configuration** - Valid tool parameters and settings\n\n### Advanced Validation Example\n\n```javascript\nclass WorkflowYAMLValidator {\n  constructor(apiKey) {\n    this.apiKey = apiKey;\n  }\n\n  async validateYAML(yamlContent, options = {}) {\n    const {\n      checkBlockConfig = true,\n      checkConnections = true,\n      checkVariables = true,\n      checkToolConfig = true\n    } = options;\n\n    try {\n      const response = await fetch('/api/workflows/validate', {\n        method: 'POST',\n        headers: {\n          'x-api-key': this.apiKey,\n          'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n        },\n        body: JSON.stringify({\n          format: 'yaml',\n          workflow: yamlContent,\n          validateBlockConfig: checkBlockConfig,\n          validateConnections: checkConnections,\n          validateToolConfig: checkToolConfig\n        })\n      });\n\n      const result = await response.json();\n      \n      return {\n        isValid: result.result.isValid,\n        errors: result.result.errors,\n        warnings: result.result.warnings,\n        summary: result.result.summary,\n        performance: result.result.performance\n      };\n\n    } catch (error) {\n      return {\n        isValid: false,\n        errors: [{ \n          type: 'error', \n          code: 'VALIDATION_FAILED', \n          message: error.message \n        }],\n        warnings: [],\n        summary: null,\n        performance: null\n      };\n    }\n  }\n\n  async validateWithDetailedReport(yamlContent) {\n    const validation = await this.validateYAML(yamlContent);\n    \n    console.log('\\n=== YAML Validation Report ===');\n    console.log(`Status: ${validation.isValid ? '✅ Valid' : '❌ Invalid'}`);\n    \n    if (validation.summary) {\n      console.log(`\\nSummary:`);\n      console.log(`- Blocks: ${validation.summary.totalBlocks}`);\n      console.log(`- Connections: ${validation.summary.totalConnections}`);\n      console.log(`- Loops: ${validation.summary.totalLoops}`);\n      console.log(`- Parallels: ${validation.summary.totalParallels}`);\n    }\n\n    if (validation.errors.length > 0) {\n      console.log(`\\n❌ Errors (${validation.errors.length}):`);\n      validation.errors.forEach(error => {\n        const location = error.location \n          ? ` (${error.location.blockName || error.location.blockId})`\n          : '';\n        console.log(`  - ${error.message}${location}`);\n      });\n    }\n\n    if (validation.warnings.length > 0) {\n      console.log(`\\n⚠️  Warnings (${validation.warnings.length}):`);\n      validation.warnings.forEach(warning => {\n        const location = warning.location \n          ? ` (${warning.location.blockName || warning.location.blockId})`\n          : '';\n        console.log(`  - ${warning.message}${location}`);\n      });\n    }\n\n    if (validation.performance) {\n      console.log(`\\nPerformance: ${validation.performance.validationTimeMs}ms`);\n    }\n\n    console.log('===============================\\n');\n    \n    return validation;\n  }\n}\n\n// Usage\nconst validator = new WorkflowYAMLValidator('YOUR_API_KEY');\nconst validation = await validator.validateWithDetailedReport(yamlContent);\n\nif (validation.isValid) {\n  console.log('YAML is ready for import!');\n} else {\n  console.log('Please fix the errors before importing.');\n}\n```\n\n## YAML Best Practices\n\n### Structure Organization\n\n<Tabs items={['Basic Structure', 'Complex Workflow', 'Reusable Components']}>\n<Tab value=\"Basic Structure\">\n```yaml\nversion: \"1.0\"\n\n# Workflow metadata (optional but recommended)\nmetadata:\n  name: \"Data Processing Pipeline\"\n  description: \"Process and analyze incoming data\"\n  version: \"1.2.0\"\n  author: \"Data Team\"\n  tags: [\"data\", \"processing\", \"automation\"]\n\n# Global variables available to all blocks\nvariables:\n  api_endpoint:\n    type: string\n    description: \"API endpoint for data submission\"\n    default: \"https://api.example.com/data\"\n  batch_size:\n    type: number\n    description: \"Number of records to process in each batch\"\n    default: 100\n\n# Workflow blocks\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Data Ingestion Trigger\"\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        startWorkflow: \"schedule\"\n        scheduleType: \"daily\"\n        dailyTime: \"09:00\"\n\n  - id: fetch_data\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"Fetch Raw Data\"\n    position: { x: 300, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        method: \"GET\"\n        url: \"{{variables.api_endpoint}}/raw\"\n        headers:\n          Authorization: \"Bearer {{secrets.api_token}}\"\n\n# Block connections\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: fetch_data\n    sourceHandle: response\n    targetHandle: input\n\n# Advanced structures (empty for basic example)\nloops: {}\nparallels: {}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Complex Workflow\">\n```yaml\nversion: \"1.0\"\n\nmetadata:\n  name: \"Customer Onboarding Pipeline\"\n  description: \"Complete customer onboarding with parallel processing\"\n\nvariables:\n  customer_data:\n    type: object\n    description: \"Customer information\"\n  welcome_email_template:\n    type: string\n    default: \"welcome_template_v2\"\n\nblocks:\n  # Entry point\n  - id: webhook_start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"New Customer Webhook\"\n    position: { x: 100, y: 200 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        startWorkflow: \"webhook\"\n        webhookPath: \"/new-customer\"\n\n  # Data validation\n  - id: validate_customer\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Validate Customer Data\"\n    position: { x: 300, y: 200 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        code: |\n          const data = inputs.webhook;\n          const required = ['email', 'name', 'company'];\n          const missing = required.filter(field => !data[field]);\n          \n          if (missing.length > 0) {\n            throw new Error(`Missing fields: ${missing.join(', ')}`);\n          }\n          \n          return {\n            customer_data: data,\n            valid: true\n          };\n\n  # Parallel processing gateway\n  - id: parallel_onboarding\n    metadata:\n      id: parallel\n      name: \"Parallel Onboarding Tasks\"\n    position: { x: 500, y: 200 }\n\n  # Email branch\n  - id: send_welcome_email\n    metadata:\n      id: gmail\n      name: \"Send Welcome Email\"\n    position: { x: 400, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        to: \"{{validate_customer.customer_data.email}}\"\n        subject: \"Welcome to our platform!\"\n        templateId: \"{{variables.welcome_email_template}}\"\n\n  # Account setup branch  \n  - id: create_account\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"Create User Account\"\n    position: { x: 400, y: 300 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        method: \"POST\"\n        url: \"{{secrets.api_base_url}}/users\"\n        body: |\n          {\n            \"email\": \"{{validate_customer.customer_data.email}}\",\n            \"name\": \"{{validate_customer.customer_data.name}}\",\n            \"company\": \"{{validate_customer.customer_data.company}}\"\n          }\n\n  # Completion\n  - id: onboarding_complete\n    metadata:\n      id: slack\n      name: \"Notify Team\"\n    position: { x: 700, y: 200 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        channel: \"#customer-success\"\n        text: \"New customer onboarded: {{validate_customer.customer_data.name}}\"\n\nconnections:\n  - source: webhook_start\n    target: validate_customer\n  - source: validate_customer\n    target: parallel_onboarding\n  - source: parallel_onboarding\n    target: onboarding_complete\n\n# Define parallel execution\nparallels:\n  parallel_onboarding:\n    config:\n      branches:\n        - name: \"Email Processing\"\n          blocks: [\"send_welcome_email\"]\n        - name: \"Account Creation\"\n          blocks: [\"create_account\"]\n      waitForAll: true  # Wait for both branches to complete\n\nloops: {}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Reusable Components\">\n```yaml\nversion: \"1.0\"\n\n# Define reusable templates and configurations\ntemplates:\n  error_handler: &error_handler\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Error Handler\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        code: |\n          console.error('Error occurred:', inputs.error);\n          // Send error notification\n          return {\n            error_logged: true,\n            timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n          };\n\n  api_call_template: &api_template\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n    config:\n      params:\n        headers:\n          Authorization: \"Bearer {{secrets.api_token}}\"\n          Content-Type: \"application/json\"\n\nvariables:\n  retry_count:\n    type: number\n    default: 3\n  timeout_ms:\n    type: number\n    default: 30000\n\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Start Process\"\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n\n  # Use template with overrides\n  - id: fetch_users\n    <<: *api_template\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"Fetch Users\"\n    position: { x: 300, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        <<: *api_template.config.params\n        method: \"GET\"\n        url: \"{{secrets.api_base_url}}/users\"\n        timeout: \"{{variables.timeout_ms}}\"\n\n  - id: process_users\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Process User Data\"\n    position: { x: 500, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        code: |\n          const users = inputs.fetch_users;\n          const processed = users.map(user => ({\n            ...user,\n            processed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n            status: 'active'\n          }));\n          \n          return { processed_users: processed };\n\n  # Error handling with template\n  - id: handle_errors\n    <<: *error_handler\n    position: { x: 500, y: 300 }\n\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: fetch_users\n  - source: fetch_users\n    target: process_users\n  # Error connection\n  - source: fetch_users\n    target: handle_errors\n    condition: \"error\"\n\nloops: {}\nparallels: {}\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Variable Management\n\n```yaml\n# Comprehensive variable definitions\nvariables:\n  # Basic types\n  api_endpoint:\n    type: string\n    description: \"Main API endpoint\"\n    required: true\n  \n  batch_size:\n    type: number\n    description: \"Processing batch size\"\n    default: 50\n    min: 1\n    max: 1000\n  \n  enabled_features:\n    type: array\n    description: \"List of enabled features\"\n    default: [\"email\", \"sms\", \"webhook\"]\n    items:\n      type: string\n  \n  # Complex objects\n  email_config:\n    type: object\n    description: \"Email configuration settings\"\n    properties:\n      smtp_host:\n        type: string\n        required: true\n      smtp_port:\n        type: number\n        default: 587\n      use_tls:\n        type: boolean\n        default: true\n      templates:\n        type: object\n        properties:\n          welcome:\n            type: string\n            default: \"welcome_template\"\n          notification:\n            type: string\n            default: \"notification_template\"\n  \n  # Environment-specific\n  debug_mode:\n    type: boolean\n    description: \"Enable debug logging\"\n    default: false\n    env_var: \"WORKFLOW_DEBUG\"  # Can be overridden by environment variable\n```\n\n### Error Handling Patterns\n\n```yaml\n# Error handling patterns in YAML workflows\nblocks:\n  - id: risky_operation\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"External API Call\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        method: \"POST\"\n        url: \"{{variables.external_api}}\"\n        timeout: 30000\n        retries: 3\n        retryDelay: 1000\n    error_handling:\n      on_error: \"continue_to_error_handler\"\n      log_errors: true\n\n  - id: error_handler\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Handle API Errors\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        code: |\n          const error = inputs.error;\n          console.error('API call failed:', error.message);\n          \n          // Determine if error is retryable\n          const retryable = error.status >= 500 || error.code === 'TIMEOUT';\n          \n          return {\n            should_retry: retryable,\n            error_message: error.message,\n            handled_at: new Date().toISOString()\n          };\n\n  - id: fallback_action\n    metadata:\n      id: slack\n      name: \"Notify on Failure\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        channel: \"#alerts\"\n        text: \"Workflow failed: {{error_handler.error_message}}\"\n\nconnections:\n  - source: risky_operation\n    target: success_handler\n    condition: \"success\"  # Only on success\n    \n  - source: risky_operation\n    target: error_handler\n    condition: \"error\"    # Only on error\n    \n  - source: error_handler\n    target: fallback_action\n    condition: \"{{error_handler.should_retry === false}}\"\n```\n\n## Version Control Integration\n\n### Git Workflow Integration\n\n<Tabs items={['Git Hooks', 'CI/CD Pipeline', 'Branch Management']}>\n<Tab value=\"Git Hooks\">\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# .git/hooks/pre-commit\n# Validate YAML workflows before commit\n\necho \"Validating workflow YAML files...\"\n\n# Find all YAML files in workflows directory\nyaml_files=$(find workflows/ -name \"*.yaml\" -o -name \"*.yml\" 2>/dev/null)\n\nif [ -z \"$yaml_files\" ]; then\n  echo \"No YAML workflow files found\"\n  exit 0\nfi\n\nvalidation_failed=0\n\nfor file in $yaml_files; do\n  echo \"Validating: $file\"\n  \n  # Read YAML content\n  yaml_content=$(cat \"$file\")\n  \n  # Validate using API\n  response=$(curl -s -X POST \\\n    -H \"x-api-key: $SIM_API_KEY\" \\\n    -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n    -d \"{\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"validation-test\\\",\n      \\\"yaml\\\": $(echo \"$yaml_content\" | jq -R -s '.'),\n      \\\"validateOnly\\\": true\n    }\" \\\n    https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/yaml)\n  \n  # Check if validation passed\n  valid=$(echo \"$response\" | jq -r '.valid // false')\n  \n  if [ \"$valid\" != \"true\" ]; then\n    echo \"❌ Validation failed for $file\"\n    echo \"$response\" | jq -r '.validationErrors[]?.message // .error'\n    validation_failed=1\n  else\n    echo \"✅ $file is valid\"\n  fi\ndone\n\nif [ $validation_failed -eq 1 ]; then\n  echo \"One or more YAML files failed validation. Commit aborted.\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\necho \"All workflow YAML files are valid!\"\nexit 0\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"CI/CD Pipeline\">\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/deploy-workflows.yml\nname: Deploy Workflows\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n    paths: ['workflows/**/*.yaml', 'workflows/**/*.yml']\n\njobs:\n  validate-and-deploy:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    \n    steps:\n    - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n    \n    - name: Validate YAML workflows\n      run: |\n        for file in workflows/*.yaml workflows/*.yml; do\n          if [ -f \"$file\" ]; then\n            echo \"Validating $file...\"\n            \n            yaml_content=$(cat \"$file\")\n            \n            response=$(curl -s -X POST \\\n              -H \"x-api-key: ${{ secrets.SIM_API_KEY }}\" \\\n              -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n              -d \"{\n                \\\"name\\\": \\\"ci-validation\\\",\n                \\\"yaml\\\": $(echo \"$yaml_content\" | jq -R -s '.'),\n                \\\"validateOnly\\\": true\n              }\" \\\n              https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/yaml)\n            \n            valid=$(echo \"$response\" | jq -r '.valid // false')\n            \n            if [ \"$valid\" != \"true\" ]; then\n              echo \"❌ Validation failed for $file\"\n              echo \"$response\" | jq -r '.validationErrors[]?.message // .error'\n              exit 1\n            fi\n            \n            echo \"✅ $file validated successfully\"\n          fi\n        done\n\n    - name: Deploy to staging\n      if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main'\n      run: |\n        for file in workflows/*.yaml workflows/*.yml; do\n          if [ -f \"$file\" ]; then\n            workflow_name=$(basename \"$file\" .yaml)\n            workflow_name=$(basename \"$workflow_name\" .yml)\n            \n            echo \"Deploying $workflow_name from $file...\"\n            \n            yaml_content=$(cat \"$file\")\n            \n            curl -X POST \\\n              -H \"x-api-key: ${{ secrets.SIM_API_KEY_STAGING }}\" \\\n              -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n              -d \"{\n                \\\"name\\\": \\\"$workflow_name\\\",\n                \\\"description\\\": \\\"Deployed from CI/CD\\\",\n                \\\"workspaceId\\\": \\\"${{ secrets.STAGING_WORKSPACE_ID }}\\\",\n                \\\"yaml\\\": $(echo \"$yaml_content\" | jq -R -s '.'),\n                \\\"overwriteExisting\\\": true\n              }\" \\\n              https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/yaml\n          fi\n        done\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Branch Management\">\n```javascript\n// workflow-manager.js - Manage workflows across branches\nclass WorkflowBranchManager {\n  constructor(apiKey) {\n    this.apiKey = apiKey;\n  }\n\n  async deployFromBranch(branch, environment) {\n    console.log(`Deploying workflows from ${branch} to ${environment}`);\n    \n    // Get workflows from git\n    const yamlFiles = await this.getYAMLFilesFromGit(branch);\n    \n    const results = [];\n    \n    for (const file of yamlFiles) {\n      try {\n        const result = await this.deployWorkflowFile(file, environment);\n        results.push({ file: file.path, success: true, result });\n        console.log(`✅ Deployed ${file.path}`);\n      } catch (error) {\n        results.push({ file: file.path, success: false, error: error.message });\n        console.error(`❌ Failed to deploy ${file.path}:`, error.message);\n      }\n    }\n    \n    return results;\n  }\n\n  async deployWorkflowFile(file, environment) {\n    const workspaceId = this.getWorkspaceForEnvironment(environment);\n    \n    const response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': this.apiKey,\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        name: file.name,\n        description: `Deployed from ${file.branch} branch`,\n        workspaceId,\n        yaml: file.content,\n        overwriteExisting: true\n      })\n    });\n\n    if (!response.ok) {\n      const error = await response.json();\n      throw new Error(error.message || 'Deployment failed');\n    }\n\n    return await response.json();\n  }\n\n  async getYAMLFilesFromGit(branch) {\n    // Implementation would integrate with git to read YAML files\n    // This is a simplified example\n    const { execSync } = require('child_process');\n    \n    const files = execSync(`git ls-tree -r ${branch} --name-only | grep -E '\\\\.(ya?ml)$'`, { encoding: 'utf8' })\n      .trim()\n      .split('\\n')\n      .filter(Boolean);\n    \n    return files.map(filePath => ({\n      path: filePath,\n      name: path.basename(filePath, path.extname(filePath)),\n      content: execSync(`git show ${branch}:${filePath}`, { encoding: 'utf8' }),\n      branch\n    }));\n  }\n\n  getWorkspaceForEnvironment(environment) {\n    const workspaces = {\n      development: process.env.DEV_WORKSPACE_ID,\n      staging: process.env.STAGING_WORKSPACE_ID,\n      production: process.env.PROD_WORKSPACE_ID\n    };\n    \n    return workspaces[environment] || workspaces.development;\n  }\n}\n\n// Usage\nconst manager = new WorkflowBranchManager(process.env.SIM_API_KEY);\n\n// Deploy from main branch to production\nconst results = await manager.deployFromBranch('main', 'production');\nconsole.log('Deployment results:', results);\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n## Common Error Scenarios\n\n### YAML Validation Errors\n\n<Tabs items={['Syntax Errors', 'Structure Errors', 'Configuration Errors']}>\n<Tab value=\"Syntax Errors\">\n```yaml\n# Common YAML syntax errors and fixes\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Inconsistent indentation\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n     name: \"Start\"  # Wrong indentation\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n\n# ✅ Correct: Consistent indentation\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Start\"  # Correct indentation\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Missing quotes for special characters\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    config:\n      params:\n        message: Hello: World  # Colon needs quotes\n\n# ✅ Correct: Quoted strings with special characters\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    config:\n      params:\n        message: \"Hello: World\"\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Invalid array syntax\nconnections:\n  - source: start,target: end  # Wrong syntax\n\n# ✅ Correct: Proper array syntax\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: end\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Structure Errors\">\n```yaml\n# Common structure errors\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Missing required fields\nblocks:\n  - metadata:  # Missing 'id' field\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Start\"\n\n# ✅ Correct: All required fields\nblocks:\n  - id: start  # Required ID field\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Start\"\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Invalid connection references\nconnections:\n  - source: nonexistent_block  # Block doesn't exist\n    target: start\n\n# ✅ Correct: Valid block references\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Start\"\n  - id: process\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Process\"\n\nconnections:\n  - source: start  # Block exists\n    target: process  # Block exists\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Duplicate block IDs\nblocks:\n  - id: processor\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Process 1\"\n  - id: processor  # Duplicate ID\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"Process 2\"\n\n# ✅ Correct: Unique block IDs\nblocks:\n  - id: processor_1\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Process 1\"\n  - id: processor_2\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"Process 2\"\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Configuration Errors\">\n```yaml\n# Common configuration errors\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Invalid block type\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: invalid_block_type  # This block type doesn't exist\n      name: \"Start\"\n\n# ✅ Correct: Valid block type\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter  # Valid block type\n      name: \"Start\"\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Missing required parameters\nblocks:\n  - id: api_call\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"API Call\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        # Missing required 'url' parameter\n        method: \"GET\"\n\n# ✅ Correct: All required parameters\nblocks:\n  - id: api_call\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"API Call\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        url: \"https://api.example.com/data\"  # Required parameter\n        method: \"GET\"\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Invalid parameter values\nblocks:\n  - id: scheduled_start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Scheduled Start\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        startWorkflow: \"schedule\"\n        scheduleType: \"invalid_type\"  # Invalid schedule type\n\n# ✅ Correct: Valid parameter values\nblocks:\n  - id: scheduled_start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Scheduled Start\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        startWorkflow: \"schedule\"\n        scheduleType: \"daily\"  # Valid schedule type\n        dailyTime: \"09:00\"\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Error Handling Example\n\n```javascript\nasync function handleYAMLImportErrors(yamlContent, workflowName) {\n  try {\n    // First validate\n    const validationResponse = await fetch('/api/workflows/validate', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        format: 'yaml',\n        workflow: yamlContent,\n        validateRequired: true,\n        validateConnections: true,\n        validateBlockConfig: true\n      })\n    });\n\n    const validation = await validationResponse.json();\n    \n    if (!validation.result.isValid) {\n      console.error('YAML Validation Failed:');\n      \n      // Group errors by type\n      const errorsByType = validation.result.errors.reduce((acc, error) => {\n        acc[error.code] = acc[error.code] || [];\n        acc[error.code].push(error);\n        return acc;\n      }, {});\n\n      // Handle different error types\n      if (errorsByType.YAML_PARSE_ERROR) {\n        console.error('YAML Syntax Errors:');\n        errorsByType.YAML_PARSE_ERROR.forEach(error => {\n          console.error(`  - ${error.message}`);\n        });\n        return { success: false, type: 'syntax', errors: errorsByType.YAML_PARSE_ERROR };\n      }\n\n      if (errorsByType.MISSING_REQUIRED_FIELD) {\n        console.error('Missing Required Fields:');\n        errorsByType.MISSING_REQUIRED_FIELD.forEach(error => {\n          const location = error.location ? ` in block ${error.location.blockName}` : '';\n          console.error(`  - ${error.message}${location}`);\n        });\n        return { success: false, type: 'required_fields', errors: errorsByType.MISSING_REQUIRED_FIELD };\n      }\n\n      if (errorsByType.CONNECTION_SOURCE_NOT_FOUND || errorsByType.CONNECTION_TARGET_NOT_FOUND) {\n        console.error('Invalid Connections:');\n        [...(errorsByType.CONNECTION_SOURCE_NOT_FOUND || []), ...(errorsByType.CONNECTION_TARGET_NOT_FOUND || [])]\n          .forEach(error => {\n            console.error(`  - ${error.message}`);\n          });\n        return { success: false, type: 'connections', errors: validation.result.errors };\n      }\n\n      // General validation failure\n      return { success: false, type: 'validation', errors: validation.result.errors };\n    }\n\n    // Validation passed, attempt import\n    const importResponse = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        name: workflowName,\n        yaml: yamlContent\n      })\n    });\n\n    if (!importResponse.ok) {\n      const error = await importResponse.json();\n      console.error('Import Failed:', error);\n      return { success: false, type: 'import', error };\n    }\n\n    const result = await importResponse.json();\n    return { success: true, workflow: result };\n\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('Unexpected error:', error);\n    return { success: false, type: 'exception', error: error.message };\n  }\n}\n\n// Usage with error handling\nconst result = await handleYAMLImportErrors(yamlContent, 'My Workflow');\n\nif (!result.success) {\n  switch (result.type) {\n    case 'syntax':\n      console.log('Please fix YAML syntax errors and try again');\n      break;\n    case 'required_fields':\n      console.log('Please add missing required fields');\n      break;\n    case 'connections':\n      console.log('Please fix connection references');\n      break;\n    case 'import':\n      console.log('Import failed:', result.error.message);\n      break;\n    default:\n      console.log('An unexpected error occurred');\n  }\n} else {\n  console.log('Workflow imported successfully:', result.workflow.id);\n}\n```\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [Validation](/docs/api/workflows/validation) - Comprehensive workflow validation\n- [Export Formats](/docs/api/workflows/export-formats) - Export workflows in multiple formats  \n- [Versioning](/docs/api/workflows/versioning) - Version control and history management\n- [Error Codes](/docs/api/error-codes) - Complete error reference"
  },
  "tool_response": {
    "type": "create",
    "filePath": "/Users/jeremyparker/Desktop/Claude Coding Projects/sim/apps/docs/content/docs/api/workflows/yaml-import-export.mdx",
    "content": "---\ntitle: YAML Import/Export\ndescription: Create and update workflows using YAML format for version control and programmatic management\n---\n\nimport { Tabs, Tab } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/tabs'\nimport { Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout'\n\n# YAML Import/Export\n\nThe Sim API supports importing and exporting workflows in YAML format, enabling version control, programmatic workflow management, and easy sharing of workflow definitions. YAML format provides a human-readable, text-based representation of your workflows.\n\n## Overview\n\nYAML workflow operations include:\n\n- **Import from YAML** - Create new workflows from YAML definitions\n- **Update from YAML** - Update existing workflows with YAML\n- **Validation Only** - Validate YAML without creating workflows\n- **Layout Generation** - Automatically position blocks when importing\n- **ID Preservation** - Maintain workflow and block IDs across imports\n\n## Import Workflow from YAML\n\nCreate a new workflow from a YAML definition.\n\n### Endpoint\n\n```http\nPOST /api/workflows/yaml\n```\n\n### Request Body\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"string (required)\",\n  \"description\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"color\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"workspaceId\": \"string (optional)\",\n  \"folderId\": \"string | null (optional)\",\n  \"yaml\": \"string (required)\",\n  \"preserveIds\": \"boolean (default: false)\",\n  \"overwriteExisting\": \"boolean (default: false)\",\n  \"validateOnly\": \"boolean (default: false)\"\n}\n```\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `name` | string | - | **Required.** Name for the new workflow |\n| `description` | string | `\"\"` | Optional description |\n| `color` | string | `\"#3972F6\"` | Hex color code |\n| `workspaceId` | string | - | Target workspace ID |\n| `folderId` | string\\|null | - | Target folder ID |\n| `yaml` | string | - | **Required.** YAML workflow definition |\n| `preserveIds` | boolean | `false` | Keep original workflow/block IDs |\n| `overwriteExisting` | boolean | `false` | Overwrite existing workflow if ID matches |\n| `validateOnly` | boolean | `false` | Only validate, don't create workflow |\n\n### YAML Structure\n\nA typical workflow YAML structure:\n\n```yaml\nversion: \"1.0\"\nmetadata:\n  name: \"Email Processing Workflow\"\n  description: \"Process incoming emails and extract data\"\n  color: \"#10B981\"\n\nvariables:\n  customer_email:\n    type: string\n    description: \"Customer email address\"\n  processed_count:\n    type: number\n    description: \"Number of emails processed\"\n    default: 0\n\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Start\"\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        startWorkflow: \"webhook\"\n        webhookPath: \"/process-email\"\n    outputs:\n      response:\n        type: { input: \"any\" }\n    \n  - id: read_email\n    metadata:\n      id: gmail\n      name: \"Read Email\"\n    position: { x: 350, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        messageId: \"{{webhook.messageId}}\"\n        markAsRead: true\n    outputs:\n      subject:\n        type: { input: \"string\" }\n      body:\n        type: { input: \"string\" }\n      sender:\n        type: { input: \"string\" }\n        \n  - id: extract_data\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Extract Customer Data\"\n    position: { x: 600, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        code: |\n          // Extract customer information from email\n          const emailBody = inputs.body;\n          const customerMatch = emailBody.match(/customer:\\s*(\\S+@\\S+)/i);\n          const customer_email = customerMatch ? customerMatch[1] : null;\n          \n          return { customer_email };\n    outputs:\n      customer_email:\n        type: { input: \"string\" }\n\n  - id: send_response\n    metadata:\n      id: gmail\n      name: \"Send Response\"\n    position: { x: 850, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        to: \"{{extract_data.customer_email}}\"\n        subject: \"Re: {{read_email.subject}}\"\n        body: \"Thank you for your email. We'll process your request shortly.\"\n\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: read_email\n    sourceHandle: response\n    targetHandle: input\n    \n  - source: read_email\n    target: extract_data\n    sourceHandle: body\n    targetHandle: input\n    \n  - source: extract_data\n    target: send_response\n    sourceHandle: customer_email\n    targetHandle: input\n\nloops: {}\nparallels: {}\n```\n\n### Examples\n\n<Tabs items={['Basic Import', 'Validation Only', 'Advanced Import', 'Overwrite Existing']}>\n<Tab value=\"Basic Import\">\n```javascript\nconst yamlWorkflow = `\nversion: \"1.0\"\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: Start\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n  - id: send_welcome\n    metadata:\n      id: gmail\n      name: Send Welcome Email\n    position: { x: 300, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        to: \"{{customer_email}}\"\n        subject: \"Welcome!\"\n        body: \"Thank you for joining us.\"\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: send_welcome\nvariables:\n  customer_email:\n    type: string\n`;\n\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Welcome Email Workflow',\n    description: 'Send welcome emails to new customers',\n    color: '#10B981',\n    yaml: yamlWorkflow\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Created workflow:', result.id);\nconsole.log('Import summary:', result.summary);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Validation Only\">\n```javascript\n// Validate YAML without creating workflow\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Test Workflow',\n    yaml: yamlContent,\n    validateOnly: true\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\n\nif (result.valid) {\n  console.log('YAML is valid!');\n  console.log('Summary:', result.summary);\n  console.log('Parsed workflow has:', {\n    blocks: result.workflow.blocks?.length || 0,\n    connections: result.workflow.connections?.length || 0,\n    variables: Object.keys(result.workflow.variables || {}).length\n  });\n} else {\n  console.error('YAML validation failed:', result.validationErrors);\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Advanced Import\">\n```javascript\n// Import with advanced options\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Customer Support Automation',\n    description: 'Handle customer support tickets automatically',\n    color: '#8B5CF6',\n    workspaceId: 'ws_customer_service',\n    folderId: 'folder_automation',\n    yaml: complexYamlWorkflow,\n    preserveIds: true, // Keep original block IDs\n    overwriteExisting: false\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Advanced import results:', {\n  workflowId: result.id,\n  blocksCreated: result.summary.blocks,\n  connectionsCreated: result.summary.connections,\n  importTime: result.importTime\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Overwrite Existing\">\n```javascript\n// Import and overwrite existing workflow\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n  method: 'POST',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    name: 'Updated Workflow',\n    yaml: updatedYamlContent,\n    preserveIds: true,\n    overwriteExisting: true // This will replace existing workflow with same ID\n  })\n});\n\nif (response.ok) {\n  const result = await response.json();\n  console.log('Successfully updated workflow:', result.id);\n} else {\n  const error = await response.json();\n  console.error('Import failed:', error.details);\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Response\n\n#### Successful Import\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"wf_abc123\",\n  \"name\": \"Welcome Email Workflow\",\n  \"description\": \"Send welcome emails to new customers\",\n  \"color\": \"#10B981\",\n  \"workspaceId\": \"ws_abc123\",\n  \"folderId\": null,\n  \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\",\n  \"updatedAt\": \"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\",\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"blocks\": 2,\n    \"connections\": 1,\n    \"loops\": 0,\n    \"parallels\": 0\n  },\n  \"importTime\": 1250\n}\n```\n\n#### Validation Only Response\n```json\n{\n  \"valid\": true,\n  \"workflow\": {\n    \"blocks\": [\n      // Parsed block objects\n    ],\n    \"connections\": [\n      // Parsed connection objects\n    ],\n    \"variables\": {}\n  },\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"blocks\": 2,\n    \"connections\": 1,\n    \"loops\": 0,\n    \"parallels\": 0\n  },\n  \"validationTime\": 450\n}\n```\n\n## Update Workflow from YAML\n\nUpdate an existing workflow with a new YAML definition.\n\n### Endpoint\n\n```http\nPUT /api/workflows/yaml?id={workflowId}\n```\n\n### Query Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `id` | string | **Required.** The workflow ID to update |\n\n### Request Body\n\n```json\n{\n  \"yaml\": \"string (required)\",\n  \"preserveMetadata\": \"boolean (default: true)\",\n  \"createCheckpoint\": \"boolean (default: true)\",\n  \"validateBeforeUpdate\": \"boolean (default: true)\"\n}\n```\n\n### Examples\n\n<Tabs items={['Update Workflow', 'Replace Structure', 'Safe Update']}>\n<Tab value=\"Update Workflow\">\n```javascript\n// Update existing workflow with new YAML\nconst updatedYaml = `\nversion: \"1.0\"\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: Start\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n  - id: process_data\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: Process Customer Data\n    position: { x: 300, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        code: |\n          // Enhanced processing logic\n          const data = inputs.customerData;\n          const processed = {\n            ...data,\n            processed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n            score: calculateScore(data)\n          };\n          return processed;\n  - id: send_notification\n    metadata:\n      id: slack\n      name: Send Notification\n    position: { x: 500, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        channel: \"#customer-updates\"\n        text: \"New customer processed: {{process_data.name}}\"\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: process_data\n  - source: process_data\n    target: send_notification\n`;\n\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml?id=wf_abc123', {\n  method: 'PUT',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    yaml: updatedYaml,\n    preserveMetadata: true,\n    createCheckpoint: true,\n    validateBeforeUpdate: true\n  })\n});\n\nconst result = await response.json();\nconsole.log('Update summary:', result.summary);\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Replace Structure\">\n```javascript\n// Completely replace workflow structure\nconst newStructure = `\nversion: \"1.0\"\n# Completely new workflow structure\nblocks:\n  - id: webhook_trigger\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: Webhook Trigger\n    position: { x: 50, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        startWorkflow: webhook\n        webhookPath: \"/new-endpoint\"\n  \n  - id: parallel_processor\n    metadata:\n      id: parallel\n      name: Process Multiple Items\n    position: { x: 250, y: 100 }\n    \n  - id: final_response\n    metadata:\n      id: response\n      name: Send Response\n    position: { x: 450, y: 100 }\n\nconnections:\n  - source: webhook_trigger\n    target: parallel_processor\n  - source: parallel_processor\n    target: final_response\n\nparallels:\n  parallel_processor:\n    config:\n      branches:\n        - name: \"Email Processing\"\n          blocks: [\"email_block\"]\n        - name: \"Data Processing\" \n          blocks: [\"data_block\"]\n`;\n\nconst response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml?id=wf_abc123', {\n  method: 'PUT',\n  headers: {\n    'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n    'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify({\n    yaml: newStructure,\n    preserveMetadata: false, // Allow workflow name/description to be updated from YAML\n    createCheckpoint: true,\n    validateBeforeUpdate: true\n  })\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Safe Update\">\n```javascript\n// Safe update with validation and error handling\nasync function safeUpdateWorkflow(workflowId, yamlContent) {\n  try {\n    // First, validate the YAML\n    const validationResponse = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        name: 'temp',\n        yaml: yamlContent,\n        validateOnly: true\n      })\n    });\n\n    const validation = await validationResponse.json();\n    \n    if (!validation.valid) {\n      console.error('YAML validation failed:', validation.validationErrors);\n      return { success: false, errors: validation.validationErrors };\n    }\n\n    console.log('YAML validation passed');\n\n    // Now perform the update\n    const updateResponse = await fetch(`/api/workflows/yaml?id=${workflowId}`, {\n      method: 'PUT',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        yaml: yamlContent,\n        preserveMetadata: true,\n        createCheckpoint: true,\n        validateBeforeUpdate: true\n      })\n    });\n\n    if (!updateResponse.ok) {\n      const error = await updateResponse.json();\n      console.error('Update failed:', error);\n      return { success: false, error: error.message };\n    }\n\n    const result = await updateResponse.json();\n    console.log('Workflow updated successfully:', result.summary);\n    \n    return { success: true, result };\n\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('Update failed with exception:', error);\n    return { success: false, error: error.message };\n  }\n}\n\n// Usage\nconst updateResult = await safeUpdateWorkflow('wf_abc123', newYamlContent);\nif (!updateResult.success) {\n  console.error('Failed to update workflow:', updateResult.error || updateResult.errors);\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"wf_abc123\",\n  \"updated\": true,\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"blocks\": 3,\n    \"connections\": 2,\n    \"loops\": 0,\n    \"parallels\": 1\n  },\n  \"updateTime\": 890\n}\n```\n\n## YAML Validation\n\nValidate YAML workflow definitions without creating or updating workflows.\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\nUse validation to test YAML definitions before importing or updating workflows. This helps catch errors early and ensures smooth imports.\n</Callout>\n\n### Validation Process\n\nThe validation process checks for:\n\n- **YAML Syntax** - Valid YAML format\n- **Schema Compliance** - Correct workflow structure\n- **Block Configuration** - Valid block types and parameters\n- **Connection Validity** - Proper source/target references\n- **Variable Dependencies** - Variable references and types\n- **Tool Configuration** - Valid tool parameters and settings\n\n### Advanced Validation Example\n\n```javascript\nclass WorkflowYAMLValidator {\n  constructor(apiKey) {\n    this.apiKey = apiKey;\n  }\n\n  async validateYAML(yamlContent, options = {}) {\n    const {\n      checkBlockConfig = true,\n      checkConnections = true,\n      checkVariables = true,\n      checkToolConfig = true\n    } = options;\n\n    try {\n      const response = await fetch('/api/workflows/validate', {\n        method: 'POST',\n        headers: {\n          'x-api-key': this.apiKey,\n          'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n        },\n        body: JSON.stringify({\n          format: 'yaml',\n          workflow: yamlContent,\n          validateBlockConfig: checkBlockConfig,\n          validateConnections: checkConnections,\n          validateToolConfig: checkToolConfig\n        })\n      });\n\n      const result = await response.json();\n      \n      return {\n        isValid: result.result.isValid,\n        errors: result.result.errors,\n        warnings: result.result.warnings,\n        summary: result.result.summary,\n        performance: result.result.performance\n      };\n\n    } catch (error) {\n      return {\n        isValid: false,\n        errors: [{ \n          type: 'error', \n          code: 'VALIDATION_FAILED', \n          message: error.message \n        }],\n        warnings: [],\n        summary: null,\n        performance: null\n      };\n    }\n  }\n\n  async validateWithDetailedReport(yamlContent) {\n    const validation = await this.validateYAML(yamlContent);\n    \n    console.log('\\n=== YAML Validation Report ===');\n    console.log(`Status: ${validation.isValid ? '✅ Valid' : '❌ Invalid'}`);\n    \n    if (validation.summary) {\n      console.log(`\\nSummary:`);\n      console.log(`- Blocks: ${validation.summary.totalBlocks}`);\n      console.log(`- Connections: ${validation.summary.totalConnections}`);\n      console.log(`- Loops: ${validation.summary.totalLoops}`);\n      console.log(`- Parallels: ${validation.summary.totalParallels}`);\n    }\n\n    if (validation.errors.length > 0) {\n      console.log(`\\n❌ Errors (${validation.errors.length}):`);\n      validation.errors.forEach(error => {\n        const location = error.location \n          ? ` (${error.location.blockName || error.location.blockId})`\n          : '';\n        console.log(`  - ${error.message}${location}`);\n      });\n    }\n\n    if (validation.warnings.length > 0) {\n      console.log(`\\n⚠️  Warnings (${validation.warnings.length}):`);\n      validation.warnings.forEach(warning => {\n        const location = warning.location \n          ? ` (${warning.location.blockName || warning.location.blockId})`\n          : '';\n        console.log(`  - ${warning.message}${location}`);\n      });\n    }\n\n    if (validation.performance) {\n      console.log(`\\nPerformance: ${validation.performance.validationTimeMs}ms`);\n    }\n\n    console.log('===============================\\n');\n    \n    return validation;\n  }\n}\n\n// Usage\nconst validator = new WorkflowYAMLValidator('YOUR_API_KEY');\nconst validation = await validator.validateWithDetailedReport(yamlContent);\n\nif (validation.isValid) {\n  console.log('YAML is ready for import!');\n} else {\n  console.log('Please fix the errors before importing.');\n}\n```\n\n## YAML Best Practices\n\n### Structure Organization\n\n<Tabs items={['Basic Structure', 'Complex Workflow', 'Reusable Components']}>\n<Tab value=\"Basic Structure\">\n```yaml\nversion: \"1.0\"\n\n# Workflow metadata (optional but recommended)\nmetadata:\n  name: \"Data Processing Pipeline\"\n  description: \"Process and analyze incoming data\"\n  version: \"1.2.0\"\n  author: \"Data Team\"\n  tags: [\"data\", \"processing\", \"automation\"]\n\n# Global variables available to all blocks\nvariables:\n  api_endpoint:\n    type: string\n    description: \"API endpoint for data submission\"\n    default: \"https://api.example.com/data\"\n  batch_size:\n    type: number\n    description: \"Number of records to process in each batch\"\n    default: 100\n\n# Workflow blocks\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Data Ingestion Trigger\"\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        startWorkflow: \"schedule\"\n        scheduleType: \"daily\"\n        dailyTime: \"09:00\"\n\n  - id: fetch_data\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"Fetch Raw Data\"\n    position: { x: 300, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        method: \"GET\"\n        url: \"{{variables.api_endpoint}}/raw\"\n        headers:\n          Authorization: \"Bearer {{secrets.api_token}}\"\n\n# Block connections\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: fetch_data\n    sourceHandle: response\n    targetHandle: input\n\n# Advanced structures (empty for basic example)\nloops: {}\nparallels: {}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Complex Workflow\">\n```yaml\nversion: \"1.0\"\n\nmetadata:\n  name: \"Customer Onboarding Pipeline\"\n  description: \"Complete customer onboarding with parallel processing\"\n\nvariables:\n  customer_data:\n    type: object\n    description: \"Customer information\"\n  welcome_email_template:\n    type: string\n    default: \"welcome_template_v2\"\n\nblocks:\n  # Entry point\n  - id: webhook_start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"New Customer Webhook\"\n    position: { x: 100, y: 200 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        startWorkflow: \"webhook\"\n        webhookPath: \"/new-customer\"\n\n  # Data validation\n  - id: validate_customer\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Validate Customer Data\"\n    position: { x: 300, y: 200 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        code: |\n          const data = inputs.webhook;\n          const required = ['email', 'name', 'company'];\n          const missing = required.filter(field => !data[field]);\n          \n          if (missing.length > 0) {\n            throw new Error(`Missing fields: ${missing.join(', ')}`);\n          }\n          \n          return {\n            customer_data: data,\n            valid: true\n          };\n\n  # Parallel processing gateway\n  - id: parallel_onboarding\n    metadata:\n      id: parallel\n      name: \"Parallel Onboarding Tasks\"\n    position: { x: 500, y: 200 }\n\n  # Email branch\n  - id: send_welcome_email\n    metadata:\n      id: gmail\n      name: \"Send Welcome Email\"\n    position: { x: 400, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        to: \"{{validate_customer.customer_data.email}}\"\n        subject: \"Welcome to our platform!\"\n        templateId: \"{{variables.welcome_email_template}}\"\n\n  # Account setup branch  \n  - id: create_account\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"Create User Account\"\n    position: { x: 400, y: 300 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        method: \"POST\"\n        url: \"{{secrets.api_base_url}}/users\"\n        body: |\n          {\n            \"email\": \"{{validate_customer.customer_data.email}}\",\n            \"name\": \"{{validate_customer.customer_data.name}}\",\n            \"company\": \"{{validate_customer.customer_data.company}}\"\n          }\n\n  # Completion\n  - id: onboarding_complete\n    metadata:\n      id: slack\n      name: \"Notify Team\"\n    position: { x: 700, y: 200 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        channel: \"#customer-success\"\n        text: \"New customer onboarded: {{validate_customer.customer_data.name}}\"\n\nconnections:\n  - source: webhook_start\n    target: validate_customer\n  - source: validate_customer\n    target: parallel_onboarding\n  - source: parallel_onboarding\n    target: onboarding_complete\n\n# Define parallel execution\nparallels:\n  parallel_onboarding:\n    config:\n      branches:\n        - name: \"Email Processing\"\n          blocks: [\"send_welcome_email\"]\n        - name: \"Account Creation\"\n          blocks: [\"create_account\"]\n      waitForAll: true  # Wait for both branches to complete\n\nloops: {}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Reusable Components\">\n```yaml\nversion: \"1.0\"\n\n# Define reusable templates and configurations\ntemplates:\n  error_handler: &error_handler\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Error Handler\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        code: |\n          console.error('Error occurred:', inputs.error);\n          // Send error notification\n          return {\n            error_logged: true,\n            timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n          };\n\n  api_call_template: &api_template\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n    config:\n      params:\n        headers:\n          Authorization: \"Bearer {{secrets.api_token}}\"\n          Content-Type: \"application/json\"\n\nvariables:\n  retry_count:\n    type: number\n    default: 3\n  timeout_ms:\n    type: number\n    default: 30000\n\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Start Process\"\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n\n  # Use template with overrides\n  - id: fetch_users\n    <<: *api_template\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"Fetch Users\"\n    position: { x: 300, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        <<: *api_template.config.params\n        method: \"GET\"\n        url: \"{{secrets.api_base_url}}/users\"\n        timeout: \"{{variables.timeout_ms}}\"\n\n  - id: process_users\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Process User Data\"\n    position: { x: 500, y: 100 }\n    config:\n      params:\n        code: |\n          const users = inputs.fetch_users;\n          const processed = users.map(user => ({\n            ...user,\n            processed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n            status: 'active'\n          }));\n          \n          return { processed_users: processed };\n\n  # Error handling with template\n  - id: handle_errors\n    <<: *error_handler\n    position: { x: 500, y: 300 }\n\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: fetch_users\n  - source: fetch_users\n    target: process_users\n  # Error connection\n  - source: fetch_users\n    target: handle_errors\n    condition: \"error\"\n\nloops: {}\nparallels: {}\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Variable Management\n\n```yaml\n# Comprehensive variable definitions\nvariables:\n  # Basic types\n  api_endpoint:\n    type: string\n    description: \"Main API endpoint\"\n    required: true\n  \n  batch_size:\n    type: number\n    description: \"Processing batch size\"\n    default: 50\n    min: 1\n    max: 1000\n  \n  enabled_features:\n    type: array\n    description: \"List of enabled features\"\n    default: [\"email\", \"sms\", \"webhook\"]\n    items:\n      type: string\n  \n  # Complex objects\n  email_config:\n    type: object\n    description: \"Email configuration settings\"\n    properties:\n      smtp_host:\n        type: string\n        required: true\n      smtp_port:\n        type: number\n        default: 587\n      use_tls:\n        type: boolean\n        default: true\n      templates:\n        type: object\n        properties:\n          welcome:\n            type: string\n            default: \"welcome_template\"\n          notification:\n            type: string\n            default: \"notification_template\"\n  \n  # Environment-specific\n  debug_mode:\n    type: boolean\n    description: \"Enable debug logging\"\n    default: false\n    env_var: \"WORKFLOW_DEBUG\"  # Can be overridden by environment variable\n```\n\n### Error Handling Patterns\n\n```yaml\n# Error handling patterns in YAML workflows\nblocks:\n  - id: risky_operation\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"External API Call\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        method: \"POST\"\n        url: \"{{variables.external_api}}\"\n        timeout: 30000\n        retries: 3\n        retryDelay: 1000\n    error_handling:\n      on_error: \"continue_to_error_handler\"\n      log_errors: true\n\n  - id: error_handler\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Handle API Errors\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        code: |\n          const error = inputs.error;\n          console.error('API call failed:', error.message);\n          \n          // Determine if error is retryable\n          const retryable = error.status >= 500 || error.code === 'TIMEOUT';\n          \n          return {\n            should_retry: retryable,\n            error_message: error.message,\n            handled_at: new Date().toISOString()\n          };\n\n  - id: fallback_action\n    metadata:\n      id: slack\n      name: \"Notify on Failure\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        channel: \"#alerts\"\n        text: \"Workflow failed: {{error_handler.error_message}}\"\n\nconnections:\n  - source: risky_operation\n    target: success_handler\n    condition: \"success\"  # Only on success\n    \n  - source: risky_operation\n    target: error_handler\n    condition: \"error\"    # Only on error\n    \n  - source: error_handler\n    target: fallback_action\n    condition: \"{{error_handler.should_retry === false}}\"\n```\n\n## Version Control Integration\n\n### Git Workflow Integration\n\n<Tabs items={['Git Hooks', 'CI/CD Pipeline', 'Branch Management']}>\n<Tab value=\"Git Hooks\">\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# .git/hooks/pre-commit\n# Validate YAML workflows before commit\n\necho \"Validating workflow YAML files...\"\n\n# Find all YAML files in workflows directory\nyaml_files=$(find workflows/ -name \"*.yaml\" -o -name \"*.yml\" 2>/dev/null)\n\nif [ -z \"$yaml_files\" ]; then\n  echo \"No YAML workflow files found\"\n  exit 0\nfi\n\nvalidation_failed=0\n\nfor file in $yaml_files; do\n  echo \"Validating: $file\"\n  \n  # Read YAML content\n  yaml_content=$(cat \"$file\")\n  \n  # Validate using API\n  response=$(curl -s -X POST \\\n    -H \"x-api-key: $SIM_API_KEY\" \\\n    -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n    -d \"{\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"validation-test\\\",\n      \\\"yaml\\\": $(echo \"$yaml_content\" | jq -R -s '.'),\n      \\\"validateOnly\\\": true\n    }\" \\\n    https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/yaml)\n  \n  # Check if validation passed\n  valid=$(echo \"$response\" | jq -r '.valid // false')\n  \n  if [ \"$valid\" != \"true\" ]; then\n    echo \"❌ Validation failed for $file\"\n    echo \"$response\" | jq -r '.validationErrors[]?.message // .error'\n    validation_failed=1\n  else\n    echo \"✅ $file is valid\"\n  fi\ndone\n\nif [ $validation_failed -eq 1 ]; then\n  echo \"One or more YAML files failed validation. Commit aborted.\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\necho \"All workflow YAML files are valid!\"\nexit 0\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"CI/CD Pipeline\">\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/deploy-workflows.yml\nname: Deploy Workflows\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main]\n    paths: ['workflows/**/*.yaml', 'workflows/**/*.yml']\n\njobs:\n  validate-and-deploy:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    \n    steps:\n    - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n    \n    - name: Validate YAML workflows\n      run: |\n        for file in workflows/*.yaml workflows/*.yml; do\n          if [ -f \"$file\" ]; then\n            echo \"Validating $file...\"\n            \n            yaml_content=$(cat \"$file\")\n            \n            response=$(curl -s -X POST \\\n              -H \"x-api-key: ${{ secrets.SIM_API_KEY }}\" \\\n              -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n              -d \"{\n                \\\"name\\\": \\\"ci-validation\\\",\n                \\\"yaml\\\": $(echo \"$yaml_content\" | jq -R -s '.'),\n                \\\"validateOnly\\\": true\n              }\" \\\n              https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/yaml)\n            \n            valid=$(echo \"$response\" | jq -r '.valid // false')\n            \n            if [ \"$valid\" != \"true\" ]; then\n              echo \"❌ Validation failed for $file\"\n              echo \"$response\" | jq -r '.validationErrors[]?.message // .error'\n              exit 1\n            fi\n            \n            echo \"✅ $file validated successfully\"\n          fi\n        done\n\n    - name: Deploy to staging\n      if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main'\n      run: |\n        for file in workflows/*.yaml workflows/*.yml; do\n          if [ -f \"$file\" ]; then\n            workflow_name=$(basename \"$file\" .yaml)\n            workflow_name=$(basename \"$workflow_name\" .yml)\n            \n            echo \"Deploying $workflow_name from $file...\"\n            \n            yaml_content=$(cat \"$file\")\n            \n            curl -X POST \\\n              -H \"x-api-key: ${{ secrets.SIM_API_KEY_STAGING }}\" \\\n              -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n              -d \"{\n                \\\"name\\\": \\\"$workflow_name\\\",\n                \\\"description\\\": \\\"Deployed from CI/CD\\\",\n                \\\"workspaceId\\\": \\\"${{ secrets.STAGING_WORKSPACE_ID }}\\\",\n                \\\"yaml\\\": $(echo \"$yaml_content\" | jq -R -s '.'),\n                \\\"overwriteExisting\\\": true\n              }\" \\\n              https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/yaml\n          fi\n        done\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Branch Management\">\n```javascript\n// workflow-manager.js - Manage workflows across branches\nclass WorkflowBranchManager {\n  constructor(apiKey) {\n    this.apiKey = apiKey;\n  }\n\n  async deployFromBranch(branch, environment) {\n    console.log(`Deploying workflows from ${branch} to ${environment}`);\n    \n    // Get workflows from git\n    const yamlFiles = await this.getYAMLFilesFromGit(branch);\n    \n    const results = [];\n    \n    for (const file of yamlFiles) {\n      try {\n        const result = await this.deployWorkflowFile(file, environment);\n        results.push({ file: file.path, success: true, result });\n        console.log(`✅ Deployed ${file.path}`);\n      } catch (error) {\n        results.push({ file: file.path, success: false, error: error.message });\n        console.error(`❌ Failed to deploy ${file.path}:`, error.message);\n      }\n    }\n    \n    return results;\n  }\n\n  async deployWorkflowFile(file, environment) {\n    const workspaceId = this.getWorkspaceForEnvironment(environment);\n    \n    const response = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': this.apiKey,\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        name: file.name,\n        description: `Deployed from ${file.branch} branch`,\n        workspaceId,\n        yaml: file.content,\n        overwriteExisting: true\n      })\n    });\n\n    if (!response.ok) {\n      const error = await response.json();\n      throw new Error(error.message || 'Deployment failed');\n    }\n\n    return await response.json();\n  }\n\n  async getYAMLFilesFromGit(branch) {\n    // Implementation would integrate with git to read YAML files\n    // This is a simplified example\n    const { execSync } = require('child_process');\n    \n    const files = execSync(`git ls-tree -r ${branch} --name-only | grep -E '\\\\.(ya?ml)$'`, { encoding: 'utf8' })\n      .trim()\n      .split('\\n')\n      .filter(Boolean);\n    \n    return files.map(filePath => ({\n      path: filePath,\n      name: path.basename(filePath, path.extname(filePath)),\n      content: execSync(`git show ${branch}:${filePath}`, { encoding: 'utf8' }),\n      branch\n    }));\n  }\n\n  getWorkspaceForEnvironment(environment) {\n    const workspaces = {\n      development: process.env.DEV_WORKSPACE_ID,\n      staging: process.env.STAGING_WORKSPACE_ID,\n      production: process.env.PROD_WORKSPACE_ID\n    };\n    \n    return workspaces[environment] || workspaces.development;\n  }\n}\n\n// Usage\nconst manager = new WorkflowBranchManager(process.env.SIM_API_KEY);\n\n// Deploy from main branch to production\nconst results = await manager.deployFromBranch('main', 'production');\nconsole.log('Deployment results:', results);\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n## Common Error Scenarios\n\n### YAML Validation Errors\n\n<Tabs items={['Syntax Errors', 'Structure Errors', 'Configuration Errors']}>\n<Tab value=\"Syntax Errors\">\n```yaml\n# Common YAML syntax errors and fixes\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Inconsistent indentation\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n     name: \"Start\"  # Wrong indentation\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n\n# ✅ Correct: Consistent indentation\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Start\"  # Correct indentation\n    position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Missing quotes for special characters\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    config:\n      params:\n        message: Hello: World  # Colon needs quotes\n\n# ✅ Correct: Quoted strings with special characters\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    config:\n      params:\n        message: \"Hello: World\"\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Invalid array syntax\nconnections:\n  - source: start,target: end  # Wrong syntax\n\n# ✅ Correct: Proper array syntax\nconnections:\n  - source: start\n    target: end\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Structure Errors\">\n```yaml\n# Common structure errors\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Missing required fields\nblocks:\n  - metadata:  # Missing 'id' field\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Start\"\n\n# ✅ Correct: All required fields\nblocks:\n  - id: start  # Required ID field\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Start\"\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Invalid connection references\nconnections:\n  - source: nonexistent_block  # Block doesn't exist\n    target: start\n\n# ✅ Correct: Valid block references\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Start\"\n  - id: process\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Process\"\n\nconnections:\n  - source: start  # Block exists\n    target: process  # Block exists\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Duplicate block IDs\nblocks:\n  - id: processor\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Process 1\"\n  - id: processor  # Duplicate ID\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"Process 2\"\n\n# ✅ Correct: Unique block IDs\nblocks:\n  - id: processor_1\n    metadata:\n      id: function\n      name: \"Process 1\"\n  - id: processor_2\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"Process 2\"\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Configuration Errors\">\n```yaml\n# Common configuration errors\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Invalid block type\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: invalid_block_type  # This block type doesn't exist\n      name: \"Start\"\n\n# ✅ Correct: Valid block type\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter  # Valid block type\n      name: \"Start\"\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Missing required parameters\nblocks:\n  - id: api_call\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"API Call\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        # Missing required 'url' parameter\n        method: \"GET\"\n\n# ✅ Correct: All required parameters\nblocks:\n  - id: api_call\n    metadata:\n      id: api\n      name: \"API Call\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        url: \"https://api.example.com/data\"  # Required parameter\n        method: \"GET\"\n\n# ❌ Incorrect: Invalid parameter values\nblocks:\n  - id: scheduled_start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Scheduled Start\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        startWorkflow: \"schedule\"\n        scheduleType: \"invalid_type\"  # Invalid schedule type\n\n# ✅ Correct: Valid parameter values\nblocks:\n  - id: scheduled_start\n    metadata:\n      id: starter\n      name: \"Scheduled Start\"\n    config:\n      params:\n        startWorkflow: \"schedule\"\n        scheduleType: \"daily\"  # Valid schedule type\n        dailyTime: \"09:00\"\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Error Handling Example\n\n```javascript\nasync function handleYAMLImportErrors(yamlContent, workflowName) {\n  try {\n    // First validate\n    const validationResponse = await fetch('/api/workflows/validate', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        format: 'yaml',\n        workflow: yamlContent,\n        validateRequired: true,\n        validateConnections: true,\n        validateBlockConfig: true\n      })\n    });\n\n    const validation = await validationResponse.json();\n    \n    if (!validation.result.isValid) {\n      console.error('YAML Validation Failed:');\n      \n      // Group errors by type\n      const errorsByType = validation.result.errors.reduce((acc, error) => {\n        acc[error.code] = acc[error.code] || [];\n        acc[error.code].push(error);\n        return acc;\n      }, {});\n\n      // Handle different error types\n      if (errorsByType.YAML_PARSE_ERROR) {\n        console.error('YAML Syntax Errors:');\n        errorsByType.YAML_PARSE_ERROR.forEach(error => {\n          console.error(`  - ${error.message}`);\n        });\n        return { success: false, type: 'syntax', errors: errorsByType.YAML_PARSE_ERROR };\n      }\n\n      if (errorsByType.MISSING_REQUIRED_FIELD) {\n        console.error('Missing Required Fields:');\n        errorsByType.MISSING_REQUIRED_FIELD.forEach(error => {\n          const location = error.location ? ` in block ${error.location.blockName}` : '';\n          console.error(`  - ${error.message}${location}`);\n        });\n        return { success: false, type: 'required_fields', errors: errorsByType.MISSING_REQUIRED_FIELD };\n      }\n\n      if (errorsByType.CONNECTION_SOURCE_NOT_FOUND || errorsByType.CONNECTION_TARGET_NOT_FOUND) {\n        console.error('Invalid Connections:');\n        [...(errorsByType.CONNECTION_SOURCE_NOT_FOUND || []), ...(errorsByType.CONNECTION_TARGET_NOT_FOUND || [])]\n          .forEach(error => {\n            console.error(`  - ${error.message}`);\n          });\n        return { success: false, type: 'connections', errors: validation.result.errors };\n      }\n\n      // General validation failure\n      return { success: false, type: 'validation', errors: validation.result.errors };\n    }\n\n    // Validation passed, attempt import\n    const importResponse = await fetch('/api/workflows/yaml', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify({\n        name: workflowName,\n        yaml: yamlContent\n      })\n    });\n\n    if (!importResponse.ok) {\n      const error = await importResponse.json();\n      console.error('Import Failed:', error);\n      return { success: false, type: 'import', error };\n    }\n\n    const result = await importResponse.json();\n    return { success: true, workflow: result };\n\n  } catch (error) {\n    console.error('Unexpected error:', error);\n    return { success: false, type: 'exception', error: error.message };\n  }\n}\n\n// Usage with error handling\nconst result = await handleYAMLImportErrors(yamlContent, 'My Workflow');\n\nif (!result.success) {\n  switch (result.type) {\n    case 'syntax':\n      console.log('Please fix YAML syntax errors and try again');\n      break;\n    case 'required_fields':\n      console.log('Please add missing required fields');\n      break;\n    case 'connections':\n      console.log('Please fix connection references');\n      break;\n    case 'import':\n      console.log('Import failed:', result.error.message);\n      break;\n    default:\n      console.log('An unexpected error occurred');\n  }\n} else {\n  console.log('Workflow imported successfully:', result.workflow.id);\n}\n```\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [Validation](/docs/api/workflows/validation) - Comprehensive workflow validation\n- [Export Formats](/docs/api/workflows/export-formats) - Export workflows in multiple formats  \n- [Versioning](/docs/api/workflows/versioning) - Version control and history management\n- [Error Codes](/docs/api/error-codes) - Complete error reference",
    "structuredPatch": []
  }
}
