    "content": "---\ntitle: Error Codes\ndescription: Complete reference for API error codes, troubleshooting, and resolution strategies\n---\n\nimport { Tabs, Tab } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/tabs'\nimport { Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout'\n\n# API Error Codes\n\nThe Sim API uses conventional HTTP status codes and provides detailed error information to help you troubleshoot issues quickly. This reference covers all error codes, their meanings, and resolution strategies.\n\n## HTTP Status Codes\n\n### Success Codes (2xx)\n\n| Code | Name | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| `200` | OK | Request succeeded |\n| `201` | Created | Resource created successfully |\n| `202` | Accepted | Request accepted for processing |\n\n### Client Error Codes (4xx)\n\n| Code | Name | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| `400` | Bad Request | Invalid request data or parameters |\n| `401` | Unauthorized | Authentication required or invalid |\n| `403` | Forbidden | Insufficient permissions |\n| `404` | Not Found | Resource not found |\n| `409` | Conflict | Resource conflict (duplicate, etc.) |\n| `422` | Unprocessable Entity | Valid syntax but semantic errors |\n| `429` | Too Many Requests | Rate limit exceeded |\n\n### Server Error Codes (5xx)\n\n| Code | Name | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| `500` | Internal Server Error | Unexpected server error |\n| `502` | Bad Gateway | Upstream service error |\n| `503` | Service Unavailable | Service temporarily unavailable |\n| `504` | Gateway Timeout | Upstream service timeout |\n\n## Error Response Format\n\nAll error responses follow a consistent structure:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Error title\",\n  \"message\": \"Detailed error description\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    // Additional error-specific information\n  },\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n## Authentication Errors (401)\n\n### Invalid API Key\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Unauthorized\",\n  \"message\": \"Invalid API key provided\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"type\": \"invalid_api_key\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Verify your API key is correct and hasn't been revoked.\n\n### Expired Session\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Unauthorized\", \n  \"message\": \"Session has expired\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"type\": \"expired_session\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Re-authenticate to get a new session.\n\n### Missing Authentication\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Unauthorized\",\n  \"message\": \"Authentication required\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"type\": \"missing_authentication\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Include `x-api-key` header or ensure session cookies are sent.\n\n## Permission Errors (403)\n\n### Insufficient Permissions\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Forbidden\",\n  \"message\": \"Insufficient permissions for this operation\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\", \n  \"details\": {\n    \"required_permission\": \"workflows:write\",\n    \"user_permission\": \"workflows:read\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Contact your workspace admin to upgrade your permissions.\n\n### Access Denied\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Access denied\",\n  \"message\": \"You don't have permission to access this workflow\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"workflow_id\": \"wf_abc123\",\n    \"owner_id\": \"user_456\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Request access from the workflow owner or join the workspace.\n\n## Validation Errors (400)\n\n### Invalid Request Data\n\n<Tabs items={['Missing Fields', 'Invalid Types', 'Validation Failed']}>\n<Tab value=\"Missing Fields\">\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Invalid request data\",\n  \"message\": \"Missing required fields\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": [\n    {\n      \"field\": \"name\",\n      \"message\": \"Name is required\",\n      \"code\": \"required\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"field\": \"workspaceId\", \n      \"message\": \"Workspace ID must be provided\",\n      \"code\": \"required\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Add the missing required fields to your request.\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Invalid Types\">\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Invalid request data\", \n  \"message\": \"Invalid field types\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": [\n    {\n      \"field\": \"limit\",\n      \"message\": \"Expected number but received string\",\n      \"received\": \"twenty\",\n      \"expected\": \"number\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"field\": \"color\",\n      \"message\": \"Must be a valid hex color code\",\n      \"received\": \"blue\",\n      \"expected\": \"#RRGGBB format\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Ensure all fields use the correct data types as specified in the API documentation.\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Validation Failed\">\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Validation failed\",\n  \"message\": \"YAML workflow validation failed\", \n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"validationErrors\": [\n      {\n        \"type\": \"error\",\n        \"code\": \"MISSING_REQUIRED_FIELD\",\n        \"message\": \"Required field 'url' is missing in block api_call\",\n        \"location\": {\n          \"blockId\": \"api_call\",\n          \"blockName\": \"API Call\",\n          \"field\": \"url\"\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Fix the validation errors in your workflow definition.\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Invalid Query Parameters\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Invalid query parameters\",\n  \"message\": \"Invalid pagination parameters\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": [\n    {\n      \"parameter\": \"limit\",\n      \"message\": \"Limit must be between 1 and 100\",\n      \"received\": 150\n    },\n    {\n      \"parameter\": \"sortBy\", \n      \"message\": \"Invalid sort field\",\n      \"received\": \"invalid_field\",\n      \"allowed\": [\"name\", \"createdAt\", \"updatedAt\", \"runCount\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Use valid parameter values as documented in the API reference.\n\n## Resource Errors (404)\n\n### Workflow Not Found\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Workflow not found\",\n  \"message\": \"No workflow found with ID wf_abc123\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"workflow_id\": \"wf_abc123\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Verify the workflow ID is correct and you have access to it.\n\n### Workspace Not Found\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Workspace not found\", \n  \"message\": \"No workspace found with ID ws_xyz789\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"workspace_id\": \"ws_xyz789\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Check the workspace ID or verify workspace membership.\n\n## Conflict Errors (409)\n\n### Duplicate Resource\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Workflow name already exists\",\n  \"message\": \"A workflow with this name already exists in the workspace\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"existing_workflow_id\": \"wf_def456\",\n    \"workspace_id\": \"ws_abc123\",\n    \"name\": \"Data Processing Pipeline\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Use a different name or update the existing workflow.\n\n### Concurrent Modification\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Concurrent modification\",\n  \"message\": \"Workflow was modified by another user\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"workflow_id\": \"wf_abc123\",\n    \"last_modified_by\": \"user_456\",\n    \"last_modified_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:25:00Z\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Refresh the workflow data and retry your changes.\n\n## Rate Limit Errors (429)\n\n### Rate Limit Exceeded\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Rate limit exceeded\",\n  \"message\": \"API rate limit exceeded. Try again in 60 seconds.\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"limit\": 1000,\n    \"window\": 3600,\n    \"retry_after\": 60\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Wait for the specified time before retrying, or implement exponential backoff.\n\n### Quota Exceeded\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Quota exceeded\",\n  \"message\": \"Monthly API quota exceeded\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"quota_limit\": 10000,\n    \"quota_used\": 10000,\n    \"quota_resets_at\": \"2024-02-01T00:00:00Z\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Upgrade your plan or wait for quota reset.\n\n## Server Errors (5xx)\n\n### Internal Server Error\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Internal server error\",\n  \"message\": \"An unexpected error occurred\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"error_id\": \"err_server_abc123\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Retry the request. Contact support if the issue persists.\n\n### Service Unavailable\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Service unavailable\",\n  \"message\": \"Workflow execution service is temporarily unavailable\", \n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"service\": \"workflow_executor\",\n    \"estimated_recovery\": \"2024-01-15T11:00:00Z\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Wait and retry. Check status page for service updates.\n\n## Workflow-Specific Errors\n\n### YAML Import Errors\n\n<Tabs items={['Syntax Error', 'Structure Error', 'Block Error']}>\n<Tab value=\"Syntax Error\">\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"YAML parsing failed\",\n  \"message\": \"Invalid YAML syntax\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"yaml_error\": \"mapping values are not allowed here\",\n    \"line\": 15,\n    \"column\": 8,\n    \"context\": \"config:\\n  params:\\n    url: invalid: syntax\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Fix YAML syntax errors. Check indentation and special characters.\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Structure Error\">\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Invalid workflow structure\",\n  \"message\": \"Workflow structure validation failed\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"validation_errors\": [\n      {\n        \"type\": \"error\",\n        \"code\": \"MISSING_BLOCKS\",\n        \"message\": \"Workflow must contain at least one block\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"type\": \"error\", \n        \"code\": \"DUPLICATE_BLOCK_ID\",\n        \"message\": \"Duplicate block ID found: processor\",\n        \"location\": {\n          \"blockId\": \"processor\"\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Fix structural issues in the workflow definition.\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Block Error\">\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Invalid block configuration\",\n  \"message\": \"Block configuration validation failed\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\", \n  \"details\": {\n    \"validation_errors\": [\n      {\n        \"type\": \"error\",\n        \"code\": \"UNSUPPORTED_BLOCK_TYPE\", \n        \"message\": \"Unsupported block type: invalid_block\",\n        \"location\": {\n          \"blockId\": \"my_block\",\n          \"blockName\": \"My Block\"\n        }\n      },\n      {\n        \"type\": \"error\",\n        \"code\": \"MISSING_REQUIRED_FIELD\",\n        \"message\": \"Required field 'url' is missing in block api_call\",\n        \"location\": {\n          \"blockId\": \"api_call\",\n          \"field\": \"url\"\n        }\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Fix block configuration errors. Check block types and required fields.\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Execution Errors\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Workflow execution failed\",\n  \"message\": \"Block execution failed during workflow run\",\n  \"requestId\": \"req_abc123\",\n  \"details\": {\n    \"execution_id\": \"exec_abc123\",\n    \"failed_block\": \"api_call\",\n    \"block_error\": \"Connection timeout\",\n    \"execution_logs\": [\n      {\n        \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:15Z\",\n        \"level\": \"info\", \n        \"block\": \"start\",\n        \"message\": \"Workflow started\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:16Z\",\n        \"level\": \"error\",\n        \"block\": \"api_call\",\n        \"message\": \"Request timeout after 30s\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Resolution**: Check block configuration and external service availability.\n\n## Error Handling Patterns\n\n### Basic Error Handling\n\n<Tabs items={['JavaScript', 'Python', 'cURL']}>\n<Tab value=\"JavaScript\">\n```javascript\nasync function handleApiRequest(url, options) {\n  try {\n    const response = await fetch(url, options);\n    \n    if (!response.ok) {\n      const error = await response.json();\n      \n      switch (response.status) {\n        case 400:\n          console.error('Bad Request:', error.message);\n          if (error.details) {\n            error.details.forEach(detail => {\n              console.error(`- ${detail.field}: ${detail.message}`);\n            });\n          }\n          break;\n          \n        case 401:\n          console.error('Authentication failed:', error.message);\n          // Redirect to login or refresh token\n          break;\n          \n        case 403:\n          console.error('Permission denied:', error.message);\n          // Show permission error to user\n          break;\n          \n        case 404:\n          console.error('Resource not found:', error.message);\n          break;\n          \n        case 409:\n          console.error('Conflict:', error.message);\n          // Handle conflicts (name exists, concurrent modification, etc.)\n          break;\n          \n        case 429:\n          console.error('Rate limited:', error.message);\n          const retryAfter = error.details?.retry_after || 60;\n          console.log(`Retrying in ${retryAfter} seconds...`);\n          await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, retryAfter * 1000));\n          return handleApiRequest(url, options); // Retry\n          \n        case 500:\n        default:\n          console.error('Server error:', error.message);\n          console.error('Request ID:', error.requestId);\n          // Contact support with requestId\n          break;\n      }\n      \n      throw new Error(`API Error (${response.status}): ${error.message}`);\n    }\n    \n    return await response.json();\n    \n  } catch (error) {\n    if (error instanceof TypeError) {\n      // Network error\n      console.error('Network error:', error.message);\n      throw new Error('Network connection failed');\n    }\n    \n    throw error;\n  }\n}\n\n// Usage\ntry {\n  const result = await handleApiRequest('/api/workflows', {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify(workflowData)\n  });\n  \n  console.log('Success:', result);\n} catch (error) {\n  console.error('Operation failed:', error.message);\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Python\">\n```python\nimport requests\nimport time\nfrom requests.adapters import HTTPAdapter\nfrom requests.packages.urllib3.util.retry import Retry\n\nclass SimAPIError(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, status_code, message, details=None, request_id=None):\n        self.status_code = status_code\n        self.message = message\n        self.details = details\n        self.request_id = request_id\n        super().__init__(f\"API Error ({status_code}): {message}\")\n\nclass SimAPIClient:\n    def __init__(self, api_key, base_url=\"https://api.sim.dev\"):\n        self.api_key = api_key\n        self.base_url = base_url\n        self.session = requests.Session()\n        \n        # Configure retries for server errors\n        retry_strategy = Retry(\n            total=3,\n            status_forcelist=[500, 502, 503, 504],\n            backoff_factor=1\n        )\n        adapter = HTTPAdapter(max_retries=retry_strategy)\n        self.session.mount(\"http://\", adapter)\n        self.session.mount(\"https://\", adapter)\n        \n    def _handle_error(self, response):\n        try:\n            error_data = response.json()\n        except ValueError:\n            error_data = {\"message\": \"Unknown error\"}\n            \n        message = error_data.get(\"message\", \"Unknown error\")\n        details = error_data.get(\"details\")\n        request_id = error_data.get(\"requestId\")\n        \n        if response.status_code == 400:\n            print(f\"Bad Request: {message}\")\n            if details and isinstance(details, list):\n                for detail in details:\n                    print(f\"  - {detail.get('field', 'unknown')}: {detail.get('message', 'unknown')}\")\n                    \n        elif response.status_code == 401:\n            print(f\"Authentication failed: {message}\")\n            \n        elif response.status_code == 403:\n            print(f\"Permission denied: {message}\")\n            \n        elif response.status_code == 404:\n            print(f\"Resource not found: {message}\")\n            \n        elif response.status_code == 409:\n            print(f\"Conflict: {message}\")\n            \n        elif response.status_code == 429:\n            print(f\"Rate limited: {message}\")\n            retry_after = details.get(\"retry_after\", 60) if details else 60\n            print(f\"Waiting {retry_after} seconds before retry...\")\n            time.sleep(retry_after)\n            return True  # Indicate retry should happen\n            \n        elif response.status_code >= 500:\n            print(f\"Server error: {message}\")\n            if request_id:\n                print(f\"Request ID: {request_id}\")\n                \n        raise SimAPIError(response.status_code, message, details, request_id)\n        \n    def request(self, method, endpoint, **kwargs):\n        url = f\"{self.base_url}{endpoint}\"\n        \n        headers = kwargs.get(\"headers\", {})\n        headers.update({\n            \"x-api-key\": self.api_key,\n            \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n        })\n        kwargs[\"headers\"] = headers\n        \n        max_retries = 3\n        for attempt in range(max_retries):\n            try:\n                response = self.session.request(method, url, **kwargs)\n                \n                if response.ok:\n                    return response.json()\n                    \n                # Handle rate limiting with retry\n                if response.status_code == 429 and attempt < max_retries - 1:\n                    if self._handle_error(response):  # Returns True for rate limit\n                        continue\n                        \n                self._handle_error(response)\n                \n            except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e:\n                print(f\"Network error: {e}\")\n                if attempt == max_retries - 1:\n                    raise SimAPIError(0, f\"Network error: {e}\")\n                time.sleep(2 ** attempt)  # Exponential backoff\n                \n        raise SimAPIError(0, \"Max retries exceeded\")\n\n# Usage\nclient = SimAPIClient(\"YOUR_API_KEY\")\n\ntry:\n    result = client.request(\"POST\", \"/api/workflows\", json={\n        \"name\": \"Test Workflow\",\n        \"description\": \"A test workflow\"\n    })\n    print(\"Success:\", result)\nexcept SimAPIError as e:\n    print(f\"API Error: {e}\")\n    if e.request_id:\n        print(f\"Contact support with Request ID: {e.request_id}\")\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"cURL\">\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n\n# Function to handle API requests with error handling\napi_request() {\n    local method=\"$1\"\n    local endpoint=\"$2\"\n    local data=\"$3\"\n    local max_retries=3\n    local retry_count=0\n    \n    while [ $retry_count -lt $max_retries ]; do\n        # Make the API request\n        if [ -n \"$data\" ]; then\n            response=$(curl -s -w \"HTTPSTATUS:%{http_code}\" \\\n                -X \"$method\" \\\n                -H \"x-api-key: $SIM_API_KEY\" \\\n                -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n                -d \"$data\" \\\n                \"https://api.sim.dev$endpoint\")\n        else\n            response=$(curl -s -w \"HTTPSTATUS:%{http_code}\" \\\n                -X \"$method\" \\\n                -H \"x-api-key: $SIM_API_KEY\" \\\n                \"https://api.sim.dev$endpoint\")\n        fi\n        \n        # Extract HTTP status code\n        http_code=$(echo \"$response\" | sed -n 's/.*HTTPSTATUS:\\([0-9]*\\)$/\\1/p')\n        response_body=$(echo \"$response\" | sed 's/HTTPSTATUS:[0-9]*$//')\n        \n        case $http_code in\n            200|201)\n                echo \"$response_body\"\n                return 0\n                ;;\n            400)\n                echo \"Error 400: Bad Request\"\n                echo \"$response_body\" | jq -r '.message'\n                return 1\n                ;;\n            401)\n                echo \"Error 401: Unauthorized\"\n                echo \"Check your API key\"\n                return 1\n                ;;\n            403)\n                echo \"Error 403: Forbidden\"\n                echo \"Insufficient permissions\"\n                return 1\n                ;;\n            404)\n                echo \"Error 404: Not Found\"\n                echo \"Resource not found\"\n                return 1\n                ;;\n            409)\n                echo \"Error 409: Conflict\"\n                echo \"$response_body\" | jq -r '.message'\n                return 1\n                ;;\n            429)\n                echo \"Error 429: Rate Limited\"\n                retry_after=$(echo \"$response_body\" | jq -r '.details.retry_after // 60')\n                echo \"Waiting $retry_after seconds before retry...\"\n                sleep \"$retry_after\"\n                ((retry_count++))\n                continue\n                ;;\n            5*)\n                echo \"Error $http_code: Server Error\"\n                request_id=$(echo \"$response_body\" | jq -r '.requestId // \"unknown\"')\n                echo \"Request ID: $request_id\"\n                \n                if [ $retry_count -lt $((max_retries - 1)) ]; then\n                    echo \"Retrying in 5 seconds...\"\n                    sleep 5\n                    ((retry_count++))\n                    continue\n                else\n                    return 1\n                fi\n                ;;\n            *)\n                echo \"Unexpected error: HTTP $http_code\"\n                echo \"$response_body\"\n                return 1\n                ;;\n        esac\n    done\n    \n    echo \"Max retries exceeded\"\n    return 1\n}\n\n# Usage examples\necho \"Creating workflow...\"\nworkflow_data='{\n    \"name\": \"Test Workflow\",\n    \"description\": \"A test workflow\"\n}'\n\nif result=$(api_request \"POST\" \"/api/workflows\" \"$workflow_data\"); then\n    workflow_id=$(echo \"$result\" | jq -r '.id')\n    echo \"Successfully created workflow: $workflow_id\"\nelse\n    echo \"Failed to create workflow\"\n    exit 1\nfi\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Advanced Error Recovery\n\n```javascript\nclass APIErrorHandler {\n  constructor(options = {}) {\n    this.maxRetries = options.maxRetries || 3;\n    this.baseDelay = options.baseDelay || 1000;\n    this.maxDelay = options.maxDelay || 30000;\n    this.retryableStatusCodes = options.retryableStatusCodes || [429, 500, 502, 503, 504];\n  }\n\n  async withRetry(fn, context = {}) {\n    let lastError;\n    \n    for (let attempt = 0; attempt < this.maxRetries; attempt++) {\n      try {\n        return await fn();\n      } catch (error) {\n        lastError = error;\n        \n        // Check if error is retryable\n        if (!this.isRetryable(error, attempt)) {\n          throw error;\n        }\n        \n        const delay = this.calculateDelay(attempt, error);\n        console.log(`Attempt ${attempt + 1} failed. Retrying in ${delay}ms...`);\n        \n        await this.sleep(delay);\n      }\n    }\n    \n    throw new Error(`Max retries (${this.maxRetries}) exceeded. Last error: ${lastError.message}`);\n  }\n\n  isRetryable(error, attempt) {\n    // Don't retry on last attempt\n    if (attempt >= this.maxRetries - 1) return false;\n    \n    // Retry server errors and rate limits\n    if (error.status && this.retryableStatusCodes.includes(error.status)) {\n      return true;\n    }\n    \n    // Retry network errors\n    if (error instanceof TypeError && error.message.includes('fetch')) {\n      return true;\n    }\n    \n    return false;\n  }\n\n  calculateDelay(attempt, error) {\n    // Use server-provided retry-after for rate limits\n    if (error.status === 429 && error.retryAfter) {\n      return Math.min(error.retryAfter * 1000, this.maxDelay);\n    }\n    \n    // Exponential backoff with jitter\n    const exponentialDelay = this.baseDelay * Math.pow(2, attempt);\n    const jitter = Math.random() * 0.1 * exponentialDelay;\n    \n    return Math.min(exponentialDelay + jitter, this.maxDelay);\n  }\n\n  sleep(ms) {\n    return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\n  }\n\n  // Transform API errors into user-friendly messages\n  getUserFriendlyMessage(error) {\n    const messages = {\n      400: \"Please check your request data and try again.\",\n      401: \"Please log in again to continue.\",\n      403: \"You don't have permission for this action. Contact your administrator.\",\n      404: \"The requested item could not be found.\",\n      409: \"This action conflicts with existing data. Please refresh and try again.\",\n      429: \"You're making requests too quickly. Please wait a moment.\",\n      500: \"Something went wrong on our end. Please try again.\",\n      502: \"Service is temporarily unavailable. Please try again.\",\n      503: \"Service is under maintenance. Please try again later.\",\n      504: \"Request timed out. Please try again.\"\n    };\n\n    return messages[error.status] || \"An unexpected error occurred. Please try again.\";\n  }\n\n  // Handle specific workflow errors\n  handleWorkflowError(error) {\n    if (error.details?.validationErrors) {\n      const issues = error.details.validationErrors\n        .map(e => `${e.location?.blockName || 'Unknown block'}: ${e.message}`)\n        .join('\\n');\n      \n      return `Workflow validation failed:\\n${issues}`;\n    }\n\n    if (error.details?.type === 'concurrent_modification') {\n      return \"Someone else modified this workflow. Please refresh and try again.\";\n    }\n\n    return this.getUserFriendlyMessage(error);\n  }\n}\n\n// Usage\nconst errorHandler = new APIErrorHandler({\n  maxRetries: 3,\n  baseDelay: 1000,\n  maxDelay: 10000\n});\n\nasync function createWorkflow(workflowData) {\n  return await errorHandler.withRetry(async () => {\n    const response = await fetch('/api/workflows', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: {\n        'x-api-key': 'YOUR_API_KEY',\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n      },\n      body: JSON.stringify(workflowData)\n    });\n\n    if (!response.ok) {\n      const error = await response.json();\n      const apiError = new Error(error.message);\n      apiError.status = response.status;\n      apiError.details = error.details;\n      apiError.retryAfter = error.details?.retry_after;\n      throw apiError;\n    }\n\n    return await response.json();\n  });\n}\n\n// Create workflow with automatic error handling\ntry {\n  const result = await createWorkflow({\n    name: \"My Workflow\",\n    description: \"Test workflow\"\n  });\n  console.log('Workflow created:', result.id);\n} catch (error) {\n  const userMessage = errorHandler.handleWorkflowError(error);\n  console.error('User-friendly message:', userMessage);\n  console.error('Technical error:', error.message);\n}\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting Guide\n\n### Common Issues and Solutions\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n**Quick Debugging**\nAlways check the `requestId` in error responses. Include this when contacting support for faster resolution.\n</Callout>\n\n#### Issue: \"Invalid API Key\"\n\n**Symptoms**: 401 Unauthorized with \"Invalid API key provided\"\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Verify API key is correctly copied (no extra spaces)\n2. Check if API key has been revoked in your dashboard\n3. Ensure you're using the correct environment (test vs live keys)\n4. Verify API key permissions match your request needs\n\n#### Issue: \"Rate Limit Exceeded\"\n\n**Symptoms**: 429 Too Many Requests\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Implement exponential backoff in your retry logic\n2. Reduce request frequency or batch operations\n3. Check if you're making redundant requests\n4. Consider upgrading your plan for higher limits\n\n#### Issue: \"YAML Parsing Failed\"\n\n**Symptoms**: 400 Bad Request with YAML syntax errors\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Validate YAML syntax using online validators\n2. Check indentation (use spaces, not tabs)\n3. Quote strings containing special characters\n4. Ensure proper list and object syntax\n\n#### Issue: \"Workflow Validation Failed\"\n\n**Symptoms**: 422 Unprocessable Entity with validation errors\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Use the validation endpoint before creating workflows\n2. Check all required fields are provided\n3. Verify block types are correct and supported\n4. Ensure all connection references are valid\n\n#### Issue: \"Concurrent Modification\"\n\n**Symptoms**: 409 Conflict during workflow updates\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Implement optimistic locking in your application\n2. Refresh workflow data before making changes\n3. Handle conflicts by merging changes or asking user to choose\n4. Use collaborative editing features for real-time updates\n\n### Debug Mode\n\nEnable debug logging to get more detailed error information:\n\n```javascript\n// Enable debug mode\nconst DEBUG_MODE = true;\n\nfunction debugLog(message, data = null) {\n  if (DEBUG_MODE) {\n    console.log(`[DEBUG] ${message}`, data ? JSON.stringify(data, null, 2) : '');\n  }\n}\n\nasync function apiCall(endpoint, options) {\n  debugLog(`Making API call to ${endpoint}`, options);\n  \n  try {\n    const response = await fetch(endpoint, options);\n    \n    debugLog(`Response status: ${response.status}`);\n    debugLog(`Response headers:`, Object.fromEntries(response.headers.entries()));\n    \n    if (!response.ok) {\n      const errorData = await response.json();\n      debugLog('Error response:', errorData);\n      throw new Error(errorData.message || 'API call failed');\n    }\n    \n    const data = await response.json();\n    debugLog('Success response:', data);\n    \n    return data;\n  } catch (error) {\n    debugLog('API call exception:', error);\n    throw error;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Error Monitoring\n\nImplement error monitoring to track and analyze API errors:\n\n```javascript\nclass ErrorMonitor {\n  constructor() {\n    this.errors = [];\n    this.errorCounts = {};\n  }\n\n  logError(error, context = {}) {\n    const errorLog = {\n      timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n      status: error.status,\n      message: error.message,\n      requestId: error.requestId,\n      endpoint: context.endpoint,\n      method: context.method,\n      userId: context.userId\n    };\n\n    this.errors.push(errorLog);\n    \n    // Count error types\n    const errorKey = `${error.status}_${error.message}`;\n    this.errorCounts[errorKey] = (this.errorCounts[errorKey] || 0) + 1;\n\n    // Send to monitoring service\n    this.sendToMonitoring(errorLog);\n  }\n\n  sendToMonitoring(errorLog) {\n    // Send to your monitoring service (DataDog, New Relic, etc.)\n    console.error('API Error:', errorLog);\n  }\n\n  getErrorSummary() {\n    return {\n      totalErrors: this.errors.length,\n      errorTypes: this.errorCounts,\n      recentErrors: this.errors.slice(-10)\n    };\n  }\n}\n\nconst errorMonitor = new ErrorMonitor();\n\n// Use in your API calls\ntry {\n  const result = await apiCall('/api/workflows', options);\n} catch (error) {\n  errorMonitor.logError(error, {\n    endpoint: '/api/workflows',\n    method: 'POST',\n    userId: currentUserId\n  });\n  throw error;\n}\n```\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [Rate Limits](/docs/api/rate-limits) - Understand and manage API usage limits\n- [Authentication](/docs/api/authentication) - Set up proper API authentication\n- [Troubleshooting](/docs/api/troubleshooting) - Advanced troubleshooting techniques\n- [SDKs](/docs/api/sdks/javascript) - Use our client libraries with built-in error handling"
