    "file_path": "/Users/jeremyparker/Desktop/Claude Coding Projects/sim/apps/docs/content/docs/api/workflows/collaborative-editing.mdx",
    "content": "---\ntitle: Collaborative Editing\ndescription: Real-time collaborative editing features for workflows including user management, permissions, and conflict resolution\n---\n\nimport { Tabs, Tab } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/tabs'\nimport { Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout'\n\n# Collaborative Editing\n\nThe Sim API provides powerful collaborative editing features that allow multiple users to work on workflows simultaneously. With real-time synchronization, granular permissions, and conflict resolution, teams can build complex workflows together efficiently.\n\n## Overview\n\nCollaborative editing in Sim includes:\n\n- **Real-time Updates** - See changes as they happen\n- **User Presence** - Know who's currently editing\n- **Granular Permissions** - Control who can view, edit, or manage workflows\n- **Conflict Resolution** - Automatic handling of simultaneous edits\n- **Version History** - Track all changes with author attribution\n- **Live Comments** - Discuss changes in context\n\n## Collaboration Permissions\n\n| Permission Level | View | Edit | Comment | Share | Delete |\n|------------------|------|------|---------|--------|--------|\n| **Viewer** | ✅ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |\n| **Editor** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |\n| **Owner** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |\n| **Admin** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |\n\n## Collaborator Management\n\n### List Collaborators\n\nGet all users with access to a workflow:\n\n<Tabs items={['JavaScript', 'Python', 'cURL']}>\n<Tab value=\"JavaScript\">\n```javascript\nasync function getCollaborators(workflowId) {\n  const response = await fetch(`/api/workflows/${workflowId}/collaborate`, {\n    method: 'GET',\n    headers: {\n      'x-api-key': 'your-api-key'\n    }\n  });\n\n  if (!response.ok) {\n    throw new Error(`Failed to get collaborators: ${response.status}`);\n  }\n\n  return await response.json();\n}\n\n// Usage\ntry {\n  const collaborators = await getCollaborators('wf_abc123');\n  console.log('Collaborators:', collaborators);\n} catch (error) {\n  console.error('Error:', error.message);\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Python\">\n```python\nimport requests\n\ndef get_collaborators(workflow_id, api_key):\n    \"\"\"Get all collaborators for a workflow.\"\"\"\n    \n    headers = {'x-api-key': api_key}\n    url = f\"https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/{workflow_id}/collaborate\"\n    \n    response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)\n    response.raise_for_status()\n    \n    return response.json()\n\n# Usage\ntry:\n    collaborators = get_collaborators('wf_abc123', 'your-api-key')\n    print(\"Collaborators:\", collaborators)\nexcept requests.exceptions.RequestException as e:\n    print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"cURL\">\n```bash\ncurl -X GET \\\n  -H \"x-api-key: $SIM_API_KEY\" \\\n  \"https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/wf_abc123/collaborate\"\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Response Example\n\n```json\n{\n  \"collaborators\": [\n    {\n      \"user_id\": \"user_abc123\",\n      \"username\": \"john_doe\",\n      \"email\": \"john@company.com\",\n      \"display_name\": \"John Doe\",\n      \"avatar_url\": \"https://avatars.example.com/john_doe.jpg\",\n      \"permission\": \"owner\",\n      \"added_at\": \"2024-01-10T14:20:00Z\",\n      \"last_active\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\",\n      \"currently_editing\": true,\n      \"cursor_position\": {\n        \"block_id\": \"processor\",\n        \"field\": \"config.transformation\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"user_id\": \"user_def456\",\n      \"username\": \"jane_smith\", \n      \"email\": \"jane@company.com\",\n      \"display_name\": \"Jane Smith\",\n      \"avatar_url\": \"https://avatars.example.com/jane_smith.jpg\",\n      \"permission\": \"editor\",\n      \"added_at\": \"2024-01-12T09:15:00Z\",\n      \"last_active\": \"2024-01-15T09:45:00Z\",\n      \"currently_editing\": false,\n      \"cursor_position\": null\n    }\n  ],\n  \"total_count\": 2,\n  \"active_editors\": 1\n}\n```\n\n### Add Collaborators\n\nInvite users to collaborate on a workflow:\n\n<Tabs items={['JavaScript', 'Python', 'cURL']}>\n<Tab value=\"JavaScript\">\n```javascript\nasync function addCollaborators(workflowId, collaborators) {\n  const response = await fetch(`/api/workflows/${workflowId}/collaborate`, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'x-api-key': 'your-api-key',\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      collaborators: collaborators,\n      notify: true,\n      message: \"You've been invited to collaborate on this workflow!\"\n    })\n  });\n\n  if (!response.ok) {\n    throw new Error(`Failed to add collaborators: ${response.status}`);\n  }\n\n  return await response.json();\n}\n\n// Usage - add multiple collaborators\ntry {\n  const newCollaborators = [\n    {\n      email: \"alice@company.com\",\n      permission: \"editor\"\n    },\n    {\n      user_id: \"user_ghi789\", \n      permission: \"viewer\"\n    }\n  ];\n\n  const result = await addCollaborators('wf_abc123', newCollaborators);\n  console.log('Added collaborators:', result);\n} catch (error) {\n  console.error('Error:', error.message);\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Python\">\n```python\ndef add_collaborators(workflow_id, collaborators, api_key):\n    \"\"\"Add collaborators to a workflow.\"\"\"\n    \n    headers = {\n        'x-api-key': api_key,\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    }\n    \n    payload = {\n        'collaborators': collaborators,\n        'notify': True,\n        'message': \"You've been invited to collaborate on this workflow!\"\n    }\n    \n    url = f\"https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/{workflow_id}/collaborate\"\n    response = requests.post(url, headers=headers, json=payload)\n    response.raise_for_status()\n    \n    return response.json()\n\n# Usage\ntry:\n    new_collaborators = [\n        {\n            'email': 'alice@company.com',\n            'permission': 'editor'\n        },\n        {\n            'user_id': 'user_ghi789',\n            'permission': 'viewer'\n        }\n    ]\n    \n    result = add_collaborators('wf_abc123', new_collaborators, 'your-api-key')\n    print(\"Added collaborators:\", result)\nexcept requests.exceptions.RequestException as e:\n    print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"cURL\">\n```bash\ncurl -X POST \\\n  -H \"x-api-key: $SIM_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"collaborators\": [\n      {\n        \"email\": \"alice@company.com\",\n        \"permission\": \"editor\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"user_id\": \"user_ghi789\",\n        \"permission\": \"viewer\" \n      }\n    ],\n    \"notify\": true,\n    \"message\": \"You'\\''ve been invited to collaborate on this workflow!\"\n  }' \\\n  \"https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/wf_abc123/collaborate\"\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Update Collaborator Permissions\n\nChange a collaborator's permission level:\n\n<Tabs items={['JavaScript', 'Python', 'cURL']}>\n<Tab value=\"JavaScript\">\n```javascript\nasync function updateCollaboratorPermission(workflowId, userId, newPermission) {\n  const response = await fetch(`/api/workflows/${workflowId}/collaborate`, {\n    method: 'PATCH',\n    headers: {\n      'x-api-key': 'your-api-key',\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      user_id: userId,\n      permission: newPermission\n    })\n  });\n\n  if (!response.ok) {\n    throw new Error(`Failed to update permission: ${response.status}`);\n  }\n\n  return await response.json();\n}\n\n// Usage - promote viewer to editor\ntry {\n  const result = await updateCollaboratorPermission(\n    'wf_abc123',\n    'user_def456', \n    'editor'\n  );\n  console.log('Permission updated:', result);\n} catch (error) {\n  console.error('Error:', error.message);\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Python\">\n```python\ndef update_collaborator_permission(workflow_id, user_id, new_permission, api_key):\n    \"\"\"Update a collaborator's permission level.\"\"\"\n    \n    headers = {\n        'x-api-key': api_key,\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    }\n    \n    payload = {\n        'user_id': user_id,\n        'permission': new_permission\n    }\n    \n    url = f\"https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/{workflow_id}/collaborate\"\n    response = requests.patch(url, headers=headers, json=payload)\n    response.raise_for_status()\n    \n    return response.json()\n\n# Usage\ntry:\n    result = update_collaborator_permission(\n        'wf_abc123',\n        'user_def456',\n        'editor',\n        'your-api-key'\n    )\n    print(\"Permission updated:\", result)\nexcept requests.exceptions.RequestException as e:\n    print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"cURL\">\n```bash\ncurl -X PATCH \\\n  -H \"x-api-key: $SIM_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"user_id\": \"user_def456\",\n    \"permission\": \"editor\"\n  }' \\\n  \"https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/wf_abc123/collaborate\"\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Remove Collaborators\n\nRemove a user's access to a workflow:\n\n<Tabs items=['JavaScript', 'Python', 'cURL']}>\n<Tab value=\"JavaScript\">\n```javascript\nasync function removeCollaborator(workflowId, userId) {\n  const response = await fetch(`/api/workflows/${workflowId}/collaborate`, {\n    method: 'DELETE',\n    headers: {\n      'x-api-key': 'your-api-key',\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify({\n      user_id: userId\n    })\n  });\n\n  if (!response.ok) {\n    throw new Error(`Failed to remove collaborator: ${response.status}`);\n  }\n\n  return await response.json();\n}\n\n// Usage\ntry {\n  const result = await removeCollaborator('wf_abc123', 'user_ghi789');\n  console.log('Collaborator removed:', result);\n} catch (error) {\n  console.error('Error:', error.message);\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Python\">\n```python\ndef remove_collaborator(workflow_id, user_id, api_key):\n    \"\"\"Remove a collaborator from a workflow.\"\"\"\n    \n    headers = {\n        'x-api-key': api_key,\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    }\n    \n    payload = {'user_id': user_id}\n    \n    url = f\"https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/{workflow_id}/collaborate\"\n    response = requests.delete(url, headers=headers, json=payload)\n    response.raise_for_status()\n    \n    return response.json()\n\n# Usage\ntry:\n    result = remove_collaborator('wf_abc123', 'user_ghi789', 'your-api-key')\n    print(\"Collaborator removed:\", result)\nexcept requests.exceptions.RequestException as e:\n    print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"cURL\">\n```bash\ncurl -X DELETE \\\n  -H \"x-api-key: $SIM_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"user_id\": \"user_ghi789\"\n  }' \\\n  \"https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/wf_abc123/collaborate\"\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n## Real-time Features\n\n### WebSocket Connection\n\nConnect to real-time collaboration events:\n\n```javascript\nclass WorkflowCollaboration {\n  constructor(workflowId, apiKey) {\n    this.workflowId = workflowId;\n    this.apiKey = apiKey;\n    this.ws = null;\n    this.handlers = {};\n  }\n\n  connect() {\n    const wsUrl = `wss://api.sim.dev/ws/workflows/${this.workflowId}/collaborate`;\n    \n    this.ws = new WebSocket(wsUrl, [], {\n      headers: {\n        'Authorization': `Bearer ${this.apiKey}`\n      }\n    });\n\n    this.ws.onopen = () => {\n      console.log('Connected to collaboration session');\n      this.send('join', { user_id: 'current_user' });\n    };\n\n    this.ws.onmessage = (event) => {\n      const data = JSON.parse(event.data);\n      this.handleMessage(data);\n    };\n\n    this.ws.onclose = () => {\n      console.log('Collaboration session closed');\n      setTimeout(() => this.connect(), 5000); // Reconnect\n    };\n  }\n\n  handleMessage(data) {\n    const handler = this.handlers[data.type];\n    if (handler) {\n      handler(data);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Register event handlers\n  on(event, handler) {\n    this.handlers[event] = handler;\n  }\n\n  // Send messages to collaboration session\n  send(type, payload) {\n    if (this.ws && this.ws.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {\n      this.ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n        type,\n        workflow_id: this.workflowId,\n        timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n        ...payload\n      }));\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Broadcast cursor position\n  updateCursor(blockId, field, position) {\n    this.send('cursor_update', {\n      block_id: blockId,\n      field: field,\n      position: position\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Broadcast content changes\n  updateContent(blockId, field, content) {\n    this.send('content_update', {\n      block_id: blockId,\n      field: field,\n      content: content,\n      change_id: this.generateChangeId()\n    });\n  }\n\n  generateChangeId() {\n    return `change_${Date.now()}_${Math.random().toString(36).substr(2, 9)}`;\n  }\n}\n\n// Usage\nconst collab = new WorkflowCollaboration('wf_abc123', 'your-api-key');\n\n// Handle real-time events\ncollab.on('user_joined', (data) => {\n  console.log(`${data.user.display_name} joined the session`);\n});\n\ncollab.on('user_left', (data) => {\n  console.log(`${data.user.display_name} left the session`);\n});\n\ncollab.on('cursor_update', (data) => {\n  console.log(`${data.user.display_name} is editing ${data.block_id}.${data.field}`);\n});\n\ncollab.on('content_update', (data) => {\n  console.log(`Content updated by ${data.user.display_name}:`, data.content);\n});\n\ncollab.connect();\n```\n\n### Collaboration Events\n\n| Event Type | Description | Payload |\n|------------|-------------|---------|\n| `user_joined` | User joined collaboration session | `{user, timestamp}` |\n| `user_left` | User left collaboration session | `{user, timestamp}` |\n| `cursor_update` | Cursor position changed | `{user, block_id, field, position}` |\n| `content_update` | Content was modified | `{user, block_id, field, content, change_id}` |\n| `selection_update` | Text selection changed | `{user, block_id, field, selection}` |\n| `comment_added` | Comment was added | `{user, comment, block_id, position}` |\n| `workflow_saved` | Workflow was saved | `{user, version, timestamp}` |\n\n## Conflict Resolution\n\n### Operational Transform\n\nSim uses Operational Transform (OT) to handle simultaneous edits:\n\n```javascript\nclass ConflictResolver {\n  constructor() {\n    this.pendingOperations = [];\n    this.appliedOperations = [];\n  }\n\n  // Apply local operation and send to server\n  applyLocalOperation(operation) {\n    // Apply to local state\n    this.applyOperation(operation);\n    \n    // Transform against pending operations\n    const transformedOp = this.transformAgainstPending(operation);\n    \n    // Send to server\n    this.sendToServer(transformedOp);\n    \n    // Track as pending\n    this.pendingOperations.push(transformedOp);\n  }\n\n  // Handle remote operation from server\n  handleRemoteOperation(operation) {\n    // Transform against local pending operations\n    let transformedOp = operation;\n    \n    for (const pendingOp of this.pendingOperations) {\n      transformedOp = this.transformOperations(transformedOp, pendingOp);\n    }\n    \n    // Apply transformed operation\n    this.applyOperation(transformedOp);\n    \n    // Update pending operations\n    this.updatePendingOperations(operation);\n  }\n\n  // Transform two operations for concurrent execution\n  transformOperations(op1, op2) {\n    // Implementation of operational transform logic\n    // This handles cases like:\n    // - Insertions at same position\n    // - Deletions of same content\n    // - Overlapping edits\n    \n    if (op1.type === 'insert' && op2.type === 'insert') {\n      if (op1.position <= op2.position) {\n        return {\n          ...op2,\n          position: op2.position + op1.content.length\n        };\n      }\n    }\n    \n    if (op1.type === 'delete' && op2.type === 'insert') {\n      if (op1.position <= op2.position) {\n        return {\n          ...op2,\n          position: op2.position - op1.length\n        };\n      }\n    }\n    \n    // Additional transform cases...\n    return op2;\n  }\n\n  applyOperation(operation) {\n    // Apply operation to local workflow state\n    switch (operation.type) {\n      case 'insert':\n        this.insertText(operation.block_id, operation.field, \n                       operation.position, operation.content);\n        break;\n      case 'delete':\n        this.deleteText(operation.block_id, operation.field,\n                       operation.position, operation.length);\n        break;\n      case 'replace':\n        this.replaceText(operation.block_id, operation.field,\n                        operation.position, operation.length, operation.content);\n        break;\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Conflict Resolution Strategies\n\n<Callout type=\"info\">\n**Automatic Resolution**: Most conflicts are resolved automatically using operational transform. Manual resolution is only needed for complex structural changes.\n</Callout>\n\n1. **Text Edits** - Automatically merged using operational transform\n2. **Block Configuration** - Last-write-wins with user notification\n3. **Structure Changes** - Manual resolution required\n4. **Concurrent Saves** - Automatic merge with conflict markers\n\n## Comments and Discussions\n\n### Add Comments\n\nAdd contextual comments to workflow elements:\n\n<Tabs items={['JavaScript', 'Python', 'cURL']}>\n<Tab value=\"JavaScript\">\n```javascript\nasync function addComment(workflowId, comment) {\n  const response = await fetch(`/api/workflows/${workflowId}/comments`, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: {\n      'x-api-key': 'your-api-key',\n      'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify(comment)\n  });\n\n  return await response.json();\n}\n\n// Usage - add comment to specific block\ntry {\n  const comment = await addComment('wf_abc123', {\n    block_id: 'processor',\n    position: { x: 100, y: 50 },\n    content: 'Should we add error handling here?',\n    mentions: ['user_def456']\n  });\n  \n  console.log('Comment added:', comment.id);\n} catch (error) {\n  console.error('Error:', error.message);\n}\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Python\">\n```python\ndef add_comment(workflow_id, comment_data, api_key):\n    \"\"\"Add a comment to a workflow.\"\"\"\n    \n    headers = {\n        'x-api-key': api_key,\n        'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n    }\n    \n    url = f\"https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/{workflow_id}/comments\"\n    response = requests.post(url, headers=headers, json=comment_data)\n    response.raise_for_status()\n    \n    return response.json()\n\n# Usage\ntry:\n    comment = add_comment('wf_abc123', {\n        'block_id': 'processor',\n        'position': {'x': 100, 'y': 50},\n        'content': 'Should we add error handling here?',\n        'mentions': ['user_def456']\n    }, 'your-api-key')\n    \n    print(f\"Comment added: {comment['id']}\")\nexcept requests.exceptions.RequestException as e:\n    print(f\"Error: {e}\")\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"cURL\">\n```bash\ncurl -X POST \\\n  -H \"x-api-key: $SIM_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"block_id\": \"processor\",\n    \"position\": {\"x\": 100, \"y\": 50},\n    \"content\": \"Should we add error handling here?\",\n    \"mentions\": [\"user_def456\"]\n  }' \\\n  \"https://api.sim.dev/api/workflows/wf_abc123/comments\"\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n## Best Practices\n\n### 1. Permission Management\n\n```javascript\n// Implement role-based permissions\nconst PERMISSIONS = {\n  viewer: ['read', 'comment'],\n  editor: ['read', 'comment', 'edit'],\n  owner: ['read', 'comment', 'edit', 'share', 'delete'],\n  admin: ['read', 'comment', 'edit', 'share', 'delete', 'manage']\n};\n\nfunction hasPermission(userRole, action) {\n  return PERMISSIONS[userRole]?.includes(action) || false;\n}\n\n// Check before allowing actions\nif (hasPermission(user.role, 'edit')) {\n  await updateWorkflow(workflowId, changes);\n} else {\n  throw new Error('Insufficient permissions');\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Conflict Prevention\n\n```javascript\n// Implement optimistic locking\nclass OptimisticLocking {\n  constructor() {\n    this.lockTimeout = 30000; // 30 seconds\n    this.activeLocks = new Map();\n  }\n\n  async acquireLock(blockId, userId) {\n    const existingLock = this.activeLocks.get(blockId);\n    \n    if (existingLock && existingLock.userId !== userId) {\n      const timeLeft = existingLock.expiresAt - Date.now();\n      if (timeLeft > 0) {\n        throw new Error(`Block locked by ${existingLock.username} for ${Math.round(timeLeft/1000)}s`);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Acquire lock\n    this.activeLocks.set(blockId, {\n      userId,\n      username: await this.getUserName(userId),\n      expiresAt: Date.now() + this.lockTimeout\n    });\n\n    // Auto-release lock\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      this.releaseLock(blockId, userId);\n    }, this.lockTimeout);\n  }\n\n  releaseLock(blockId, userId) {\n    const lock = this.activeLocks.get(blockId);\n    if (lock && lock.userId === userId) {\n      this.activeLocks.delete(blockId);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 3. User Presence\n\n```javascript\n// Track active users and their status\nclass PresenceManager {\n  constructor(workflowId) {\n    this.workflowId = workflowId;\n    this.activeUsers = new Map();\n  }\n\n  updatePresence(userId, status) {\n    this.activeUsers.set(userId, {\n      ...status,\n      lastSeen: Date.now()\n    });\n\n    // Broadcast to other users\n    this.broadcastPresence(userId, status);\n  }\n\n  getActiveUsers() {\n    const now = Date.now();\n    const activeThreshold = 60000; // 1 minute\n    \n    return Array.from(this.activeUsers.entries())\n      .filter(([_, presence]) => now - presence.lastSeen < activeThreshold)\n      .map(([userId, presence]) => ({ userId, ...presence }));\n  }\n\n  broadcastPresence(userId, status) {\n    // Send via WebSocket to all collaborators\n    this.broadcast('presence_update', {\n      user_id: userId,\n      status: status,\n      timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n    });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [Versioning](/docs/api/workflows/versioning) - Track workflow version history\n- [Error Codes](/docs/api/error-codes) - Handle collaboration errors\n- [WebSocket API](/docs/api/websockets) - Real-time communication details\n- [SDKs](/docs/api/sdks/javascript) - Client libraries with collaboration features"
