  "tool_input": {
    "file_path": "/Users/jeremyparker/Desktop/Claude Coding Projects/sim/apps/docs/content/docs/sdks/javascript.mdx",
    "content": "---\ntitle: JavaScript SDK\ndescription: Official JavaScript SDK for the Sim API with TypeScript support, automatic retries, and comprehensive workflow management\n---\n\nimport { Tabs, Tab } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/tabs'\nimport { Callout } from 'fumadocs-ui/components/callout'\n\n# JavaScript SDK\n\nThe official Sim JavaScript SDK provides a comprehensive, type-safe interface to the Sim API. Built with modern JavaScript and full TypeScript support, it includes automatic retries, error handling, and real-time collaboration features.\n\n## Installation\n\n<Tabs items={['npm', 'yarn', 'pnpm', 'bun']}>\n<Tab value=\"npm\">\n```bash\nnpm install @sim/sdk\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"yarn\">\n```bash\nyarn add @sim/sdk\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"pnpm\">\n```bash\npnpm add @sim/sdk\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"bun\">\n```bash\nbun add @sim/sdk\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### Initialize the Client\n\n```javascript\nimport { SimClient } from '@sim/sdk';\n\n// Initialize with API key\nconst sim = new SimClient({\n  apiKey: 'your-api-key',\n  baseUrl: 'https://api.sim.dev', // Optional, defaults to production\n  timeout: 30000, // Optional, defaults to 30 seconds\n  retries: 3 // Optional, defaults to 3 retries\n});\n\n// Or use environment variable SIM_API_KEY\nconst sim = new SimClient();\n```\n\n### Basic Workflow Operations\n\n```javascript\n// Create a new workflow\nconst workflow = await sim.workflows.create({\n  name: 'Data Processing Pipeline',\n  description: 'Processes incoming data',\n  workspaceId: 'ws_abc123'\n});\n\nconsole.log('Created workflow:', workflow.id);\n\n// Get workflow by ID\nconst retrieved = await sim.workflows.get(workflow.id);\n\n// Update workflow\nconst updated = await sim.workflows.update(workflow.id, {\n  description: 'Enhanced data processing pipeline'\n});\n\n// List workflows with filtering\nconst workflows = await sim.workflows.list({\n  workspaceId: 'ws_abc123',\n  status: 'active',\n  limit: 20\n});\n\n// Delete workflow\nawait sim.workflows.delete(workflow.id);\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Client Options\n\n```typescript\ninterface SimClientOptions {\n  apiKey?: string;           // API key (or set SIM_API_KEY env var)\n  baseUrl?: string;          // Base URL for API (default: https://api.sim.dev)\n  timeout?: number;          // Request timeout in milliseconds (default: 30000)\n  retries?: number;          // Number of retry attempts (default: 3)\n  retryDelay?: number;       // Base delay between retries in ms (default: 1000)\n  maxRetryDelay?: number;    // Maximum retry delay in ms (default: 10000)\n  userAgent?: string;        // Custom user agent string\n  debug?: boolean;           // Enable debug logging (default: false)\n}\n```\n\n### Advanced Configuration\n\n```javascript\nconst sim = new SimClient({\n  apiKey: 'your-api-key',\n  timeout: 60000,\n  retries: 5,\n  retryDelay: 2000,\n  debug: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development',\n  \n  // Custom retry logic\n  shouldRetry: (error, attempt) => {\n    if (attempt >= 5) return false;\n    return [429, 500, 502, 503, 504].includes(error.status);\n  },\n  \n  // Custom retry delay calculation\n  getRetryDelay: (attempt, error) => {\n    if (error.status === 429) {\n      // Use server-provided retry-after header\n      return error.retryAfter * 1000;\n    }\n    // Exponential backoff with jitter\n    return Math.min(1000 * Math.pow(2, attempt) + Math.random() * 1000, 30000);\n  }\n});\n```\n\n## Workflow Management\n\n### CRUD Operations\n\n<Tabs items={['Create', 'Read', 'Update', 'Delete']}>\n<Tab value=\"Create\">\n```javascript\n// Create workflow with full configuration\nconst workflow = await sim.workflows.create({\n  name: 'API Data Processor',\n  description: 'Fetches and processes API data',\n  workspaceId: 'ws_abc123',\n  tags: ['data', 'api', 'processing'],\n  color: '#4F46E5',\n  blocks: [\n    {\n      id: 'api_fetch',\n      type: 'api_call',\n      name: 'Fetch Data',\n      config: {\n        url: 'https://api.example.com/data',\n        method: 'GET',\n        headers: {\n          'Content-Type': 'application/json'\n        }\n      },\n      position: { x: 100, y: 100 }\n    },\n    {\n      id: 'processor',\n      type: 'transform',\n      name: 'Process Data',\n      config: {\n        transformation: 'return data.map(item => ({ id: item.id, processed: true }))'\n      },\n      position: { x: 300, y: 100 }\n    }\n  ],\n  connections: [\n    {\n      from: 'api_fetch.output',\n      to: 'processor.input'\n    }\n  ]\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Read\">\n```javascript\n// Get single workflow\nconst workflow = await sim.workflows.get('wf_abc123');\n\n// Get workflow with specific fields\nconst partial = await sim.workflows.get('wf_abc123', {\n  fields: ['name', 'description', 'blocks', 'updatedAt']\n});\n\n// List workflows with advanced filtering\nconst workflows = await sim.workflows.list({\n  workspaceId: 'ws_abc123',\n  status: ['active', 'draft'],\n  tags: ['data-processing'],\n  author: 'user_abc123',\n  createdAfter: '2024-01-01T00:00:00Z',\n  sortBy: 'updatedAt',\n  sortOrder: 'desc',\n  limit: 50,\n  offset: 0\n});\n\n// Search workflows by name/description\nconst searchResults = await sim.workflows.search({\n  query: 'data processing',\n  workspaceId: 'ws_abc123',\n  limit: 10\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Update\">\n```javascript\n// Update workflow properties\nconst updated = await sim.workflows.update('wf_abc123', {\n  name: 'Enhanced Data Processor',\n  description: 'Now with error handling',\n  tags: ['data', 'api', 'processing', 'enhanced']\n});\n\n// Patch specific fields\nconst patched = await sim.workflows.patch('wf_abc123', {\n  color: '#059669',\n  'metadata.lastModifiedBy': 'user_def456'\n});\n\n// Update workflow blocks\nconst withNewBlocks = await sim.workflows.updateBlocks('wf_abc123', {\n  blocks: [\n    {\n      id: 'error_handler',\n      type: 'error_handling',\n      name: 'Handle Errors',\n      config: {\n        retryCount: 3,\n        notifyOnError: true\n      },\n      position: { x: 500, y: 100 }\n    }\n  ],\n  connections: [\n    {\n      from: 'processor.error',\n      to: 'error_handler.input'\n    }\n  ]\n});\n```\n</Tab>\n<Tab value=\"Delete\">\n```javascript\n// Delete single workflow\nawait sim.workflows.delete('wf_abc123');\n\n// Delete with confirmation\nawait sim.workflows.delete('wf_abc123', {\n  confirm: true,\n  reason: 'No longer needed'\n});\n\n// Bulk delete workflows\nawait sim.workflows.bulkDelete(['wf_abc123', 'wf_def456'], {\n  force: false, // Set to true to skip confirmations\n  backup: true  // Create backup before deletion\n});\n\n// Soft delete (mark as deleted but keep data)\nawait sim.workflows.softDelete('wf_abc123', {\n  reason: 'Temporary removal for testing'\n});\n\n// Restore soft-deleted workflow\nawait sim.workflows.restore('wf_abc123');\n```\n</Tab>\n</Tabs>\n\n### Bulk Operations\n\n```javascript\n// Bulk operations with progress tracking\nconst bulkOperation = await sim.workflows.bulkOperation({\n  operation: 'move',\n  workflowIds: ['wf_001', 'wf_002', 'wf_003'],\n  targetWorkspaceId: 'ws_new123',\n  options: {\n    preserveConnections: true,\n    updateReferences: true\n  }\n});\n\n// Monitor bulk operation progress\nconst status = await sim.workflows.getBulkOperationStatus(bulkOperation.id);\nconsole.log(`Progress: ${status.completed}/${status.total}`);\n\n// Bulk update tags\nawait sim.workflows.bulkUpdateTags(['wf_001', 'wf_002'], {\n  addTags: ['production', 'v2'],\n  removeTags: ['beta']\n});\n\n// Bulk deploy workflows\nconst deployResult = await sim.workflows.bulkDeploy(['wf_001', 'wf_002'], {\n  environment: 'production',\n  waitForCompletion: true\n});\n```\n\n## YAML Import/Export\n\n### Import Workflows\n\n```javascript\n// Import from YAML string\nconst yamlContent = `\nname: Sample Workflow\ndescription: A simple workflow\nblocks:\n  - id: start\n    type: trigger\n    name: Start\n`;\n\nconst imported = await sim.workflows.importYaml(yamlContent, {\n  workspaceId: 'ws_abc123',\n  validateOnly: false,\n  overwriteExisting: false\n});\n\n// Import from file\nimport { readFile } from 'fs/promises';\n\nconst yamlFile = await readFile('./workflow.yaml', 'utf8');\nconst workflow = await sim.workflows.importYaml(yamlFile, {\n  workspaceId: 'ws_abc123'\n});\n\n// Validate YAML before import\nconst validation = await sim.workflows.validateYaml(yamlContent);\nif (!validation.isValid) {\n  console.error('Validation errors:', validation.errors);\n} else {\n  const imported = await sim.workflows.importYaml(yamlContent);\n}\n```\n\n### Export Workflows\n\n```javascript\n// Export single workflow as YAML\nconst yamlContent = await sim.workflows.exportYaml('wf_abc123');\nconsole.log(yamlContent);\n\n// Export as JSON\nconst jsonContent = await sim.workflows.exportJson('wf_abc123');\n\n// Export multiple workflows as ZIP\nconst zipBuffer = await sim.workflows.exportZip(['wf_001', 'wf_002'], {\n  format: 'yaml',\n  includeMetadata: true\n});\n\n// Save ZIP to file\nimport { writeFile } from 'fs/promises';\nawait writeFile('./workflows.zip', zipBuffer);\n\n// Export entire workspace\nconst workspaceZip = await sim.workflows.exportWorkspace('ws_abc123', {\n  format: 'yaml',\n  includeVersionHistory: false\n});\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Comprehensive Error Handling\n\n```javascript\nimport { SimError, ValidationError, NetworkError, RateLimitError } from '@sim/sdk';\n\ntry {\n  const workflow = await sim.workflows.create(workflowData);\n} catch (error) {\n  if (error instanceof ValidationError) {\n    console.error('Validation failed:', error.validationErrors);\n    error.validationErrors.forEach(err => {\n      console.error(`- ${err.field}: ${err.message}`);\n    });\n  } else if (error instanceof RateLimitError) {\n    console.error('Rate limited. Retry after:', error.retryAfter);\n    // Wait and retry\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      // Retry the operation\n    }, error.retryAfter * 1000);\n  } else if (error instanceof NetworkError) {\n    console.error('Network error:', error.message);\n    // Handle network issues\n  } else if (error instanceof SimError) {\n    console.error('API error:', error.message);\n    console.error('Request ID:', error.requestId);\n  } else {\n    console.error('Unexpected error:', error);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Custom Error Handling\n\n```javascript\n// Global error handler\nsim.onError((error, context) => {\n  console.error('SDK Error:', {\n    error: error.message,\n    context: context,\n    requestId: error.requestId,\n    timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n  });\n\n  // Send to monitoring service\n  if (error instanceof SimError && error.status >= 500) {\n    monitoring.captureException(error, { \n      extra: { context, requestId: error.requestId }\n    });\n  }\n});\n\n// Retry configuration\nsim.configure({\n  retryCondition: (error, attempt) => {\n    // Custom retry logic\n    if (error instanceof RateLimitError) return attempt < 5;\n    if (error instanceof NetworkError) return attempt < 3;\n    return false;\n  }\n});\n```\n\n## Collaboration Features\n\n### Real-time Collaboration\n\n```javascript\n// Join collaboration session\nconst collaboration = await sim.workflows.collaborate('wf_abc123');\n\n// Listen for events\ncollaboration.on('userJoined', (user) => {\n  console.log(`${user.displayName} joined`);\n});\n\ncollaboration.on('contentChanged', (change) => {\n  console.log('Content updated:', change);\n});\n\ncollaboration.on('cursorMoved', (cursor) => {\n  console.log(`${cursor.user.displayName} is editing ${cursor.blockId}`);\n});\n\n// Send updates\ncollaboration.updateContent('block_123', 'config.url', 'https://api.example.com');\ncollaboration.updateCursor('block_123', 'config.url', { line: 1, column: 10 });\n\n// Add collaborators\nawait collaboration.addCollaborator({\n  email: 'user@company.com',\n  permission: 'editor'\n});\n\n// Manage permissions\nawait collaboration.updatePermission('user_123', 'owner');\n\n// Leave session\ncollaboration.disconnect();\n```\n\n### Comments and Discussions\n\n```javascript\n// Add comment to workflow element\nconst comment = await sim.workflows.addComment('wf_abc123', {\n  blockId: 'processor',\n  position: { x: 100, y: 50 },\n  content: 'Should we add validation here?',\n  mentions: ['user_def456']\n});\n\n// Reply to comment\nawait sim.workflows.replyToComment(comment.id, {\n  content: 'Yes, good idea! I\\'ll add input validation.',\n  mentions: ['user_abc123']\n});\n\n// Get comments for workflow\nconst comments = await sim.workflows.getComments('wf_abc123');\n\n// Resolve comment thread\nawait sim.workflows.resolveComment(comment.id);\n```\n\n## Version Management\n\n### Version Control\n\n```javascript\n// Get version history\nconst versions = await sim.workflows.getVersions('wf_abc123', {\n  limit: 20,\n  includeDrafts: false\n});\n\n// Create tagged version\nconst tag = await sim.workflows.createTag('wf_abc123', {\n  tag: 'v1.2.0',\n  message: 'Production release',\n  releaseNotes: 'Added error handling and performance improvements'\n});\n\n// Restore previous version\nconst restored = await sim.workflows.restoreVersion('wf_abc123', 'v_abc123_015', {\n  createBackup: true,\n  message: 'Rollback due to issues'\n});\n\n// Compare versions\nconst diff = await sim.workflows.compareVersions('wf_abc123', {\n  fromVersion: 'v1.1.0',\n  toVersion: 'v1.2.0',\n  includeContentDiff: true\n});\n\nconsole.log('Changes:', diff.summary);\n```\n\n## Advanced Features\n\n### Streaming and Pagination\n\n```javascript\n// Stream large result sets\nconst stream = sim.workflows.streamList({\n  workspaceId: 'ws_abc123',\n  batchSize: 100\n});\n\nfor await (const batch of stream) {\n  console.log(`Processing ${batch.length} workflows`);\n  batch.forEach(workflow => {\n    // Process each workflow\n  });\n}\n\n// Auto-paginate through all results\nconst allWorkflows = [];\nfor await (const workflow of sim.workflows.iterateAll({ workspaceId: 'ws_abc123' })) {\n  allWorkflows.push(workflow);\n}\n```\n\n### Webhooks\n\n```javascript\n// Register webhook\nconst webhook = await sim.webhooks.create({\n  url: 'https://your-app.com/webhooks/sim',\n  events: ['workflow.created', 'workflow.executed', 'workflow.failed'],\n  secret: 'your-webhook-secret',\n  active: true\n});\n\n// Validate webhook signatures\nimport { validateWebhookSignature } from '@sim/sdk';\n\napp.post('/webhooks/sim', (req, res) => {\n  const signature = req.headers['x-sim-signature'];\n  const payload = req.body;\n  \n  if (!validateWebhookSignature(payload, signature, 'your-webhook-secret')) {\n    return res.status(401).send('Invalid signature');\n  }\n  \n  // Process webhook\n  console.log('Webhook received:', payload);\n  res.status(200).send('OK');\n});\n```\n\n### Caching\n\n```javascript\n// Enable caching for better performance\nconst sim = new SimClient({\n  apiKey: 'your-api-key',\n  cache: {\n    enabled: true,\n    ttl: 300, // 5 minutes\n    maxSize: 100, // Max 100 cached items\n    keyGenerator: (method, url, params) => `${method}:${url}:${JSON.stringify(params)}`\n  }\n});\n\n// Manual cache control\nawait sim.cache.clear(); // Clear all cache\nawait sim.cache.delete('workflows:list'); // Clear specific cache\nconst cached = await sim.cache.get('workflows:wf_abc123'); // Get cached item\n```\n\n## TypeScript Support\n\n### Type Definitions\n\n```typescript\nimport { SimClient, Workflow, WorkflowBlock, CreateWorkflowRequest } from '@sim/sdk';\n\ninterface CustomBlock extends WorkflowBlock {\n  type: 'custom_transform';\n  config: {\n    transformation: string;\n    timeout: number;\n  };\n}\n\ninterface CustomWorkflow extends Workflow {\n  blocks: CustomBlock[];\n  metadata: {\n    environment: 'development' | 'staging' | 'production';\n    version: string;\n  };\n}\n\n// Type-safe workflow creation\nconst createCustomWorkflow = async (data: CreateWorkflowRequest<CustomWorkflow>) => {\n  const sim = new SimClient();\n  return await sim.workflows.create(data);\n};\n```\n\n### Generic Types\n\n```typescript\n// Generic workflow type with custom metadata\ninterface WorkflowWithMetadata<T = Record<string, any>> extends Workflow {\n  metadata: T;\n}\n\ninterface ProductionMetadata {\n  environment: 'production';\n  deployedBy: string;\n  deployedAt: string;\n  version: string;\n}\n\n// Type-safe workflow operations\nconst deployToProduction = async (workflowId: string) => {\n  const workflow = await sim.workflows.get<WorkflowWithMetadata<ProductionMetadata>>(workflowId);\n  \n  if (workflow.metadata.environment !== 'production') {\n    throw new Error('Workflow not configured for production');\n  }\n  \n  return await sim.workflows.deploy(workflowId, {\n    environment: 'production'\n  });\n};\n```\n\n## Best Practices\n\n### Connection Management\n\n```javascript\n// Use connection pooling for better performance\nconst sim = new SimClient({\n  apiKey: 'your-api-key',\n  http: {\n    keepAlive: true,\n    maxSockets: 10,\n    maxFreeSockets: 5\n  }\n});\n\n// Graceful shutdown\nprocess.on('SIGTERM', async () => {\n  await sim.disconnect();\n  process.exit(0);\n});\n```\n\n### Error Recovery\n\n```javascript\n// Implement circuit breaker pattern\nclass CircuitBreaker {\n  constructor(threshold = 5, timeout = 60000) {\n    this.threshold = threshold;\n    this.timeout = timeout;\n    this.failures = 0;\n    this.lastFailTime = 0;\n    this.state = 'closed'; // closed, open, half-open\n  }\n\n  async execute(fn) {\n    if (this.state === 'open') {\n      if (Date.now() - this.lastFailTime > this.timeout) {\n        this.state = 'half-open';\n      } else {\n        throw new Error('Circuit breaker is open');\n      }\n    }\n\n    try {\n      const result = await fn();\n      this.onSuccess();\n      return result;\n    } catch (error) {\n      this.onFailure();\n      throw error;\n    }\n  }\n\n  onSuccess() {\n    this.failures = 0;\n    this.state = 'closed';\n  }\n\n  onFailure() {\n    this.failures++;\n    this.lastFailTime = Date.now();\n    if (this.failures >= this.threshold) {\n      this.state = 'open';\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n// Use circuit breaker with SDK\nconst circuitBreaker = new CircuitBreaker();\n\nconst safeApiCall = async () => {\n  return await circuitBreaker.execute(async () => {\n    return await sim.workflows.list();\n  });\n};\n```\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [Python SDK](/docs/sdks/python) - Official Python client library\n- [TypeScript SDK](/docs/sdks/typescript) - Enhanced TypeScript support\n- [API Reference](/docs/api/overview) - Complete API documentation\n- [Examples](https://github.com/sim-dev/examples) - Sample implementations and use cases"
